title: tuna loaf
directions: Melt margarine in hot milk.
Add fish, crumbs and seasonings. Add eggs, sour cream, grated carrots and frozen peas.
Mix well and put in greased 8 x 8-inch or 5 x 7-inch pan.
Sprinkle lightly with cornflake crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix in bowl the soups, milk, chili sauce, peppers, olives and browned beef.
In wide casserole, layer tortillas, beef mixture and cheese.
Start with tortillas and end with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes uncovered and 10 minutes covered.

title: dirt cake
directions: Beat butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy. In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk as directed on package. Fold in Cool Whip and add to cream cheese mixture.
Crush Oreos and layer in bowl.
Pile on creamy mixture.
Chill until set.

title: addie's chicken salad
directions: Debone chicken. Add chopped celery and pickles. Add pimiento, salt and pepper. Mix well with mayonnaise.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Thoroughly mix dry pudding with can crushed pineapple.
Mix completely.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Add marshmallows and mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green beans and burger bake
directions: Cook ground beef and onions until meat loses color.
Stir to crumble.
Add seasoning, rice and 1/2 cup cheese.
Turn into buttered, 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with drained green beans and pimentos.
Blend soup, mayonnaise, milk and lemon juice.
Pour over beans.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: diet strawberry freeze
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in blender and blend.
With blender in operation, drop in frozen berries, one at a time, into blender. Mix will become thicker.
Makes 2 servings.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: Do not take skin off of chicken.
Pound chicken breast to make larger.
Put stuffing in center of chicken; roll and secure with toothpicks.
Brown in skillet; remove when brown and put into baking dish.
Mix soup as directed on can.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with potatoes and vegetables.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl, stirring well. Pour into a greased 9-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hanky pank sandwiches
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage and add Velveeta cheese.
Put cheese and meat mixture on small party-style bread (any kind). Toast in oven at 325° for approximately 10 minutes.
Freezes very well.

title: sweet and easy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or in microwave.
Stir in other ingredients until covered with chocolate.
Drop onto cookie sheet in bite size pieces.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday goodies(7 layer cookie)
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan in a 350° oven as it heats.
Remove pan from oven and add crumbs.
Stir into butter. Mix and pat out in an even layer.
Sprinkle nuts, chips and coconut evenly in layers.
Drizzle or spoon milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Partially cool and cut into squares.

title: cherry cheese tarts
directions: Put paper cup cake holders in muffin tins.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in the bottom of each paper cup.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla together.
Put one large spoon of filling on top of vanilla wafer or until 3/4 full.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool and spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Makes 18 to 20 tarts.

title: three bean salad
directions: Toss lightly.
Take care not to break jelly beans.
Serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 4.
Choose colors of jelly beans to fit the season.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, add buttermilk, oil, eggs and food coloring.
Pour into 3 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Add Icing.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add pineapple.
Let chill until syrupy.
Add can of cherry pie filling and let set until congealed.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Put on top of congealed salad.
Sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven saute celery and onion in the oil for about 1-2 minutes or until the onions are tender. Don't brown them. Add the potatoes, water, butter, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Reduce the heat to medium high and cook until the potatoes are fork tender, not mushy.

title: frozen peaches for pies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Sprinkle lemon juice over peaches. Add dry ingredients.
Lightly stir.
Put in 8-inch pie plates, cover and freeze.

title: camper's hot chocolate
directions: Mix well in large pan.
Seal in airtight cans.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons in cup and add boiling water and marshmallows. Delicious sitting around the campfire.

title: crab smash
directions: Spread cream cheese 1/4-inch thick on platter.
Pour and spread cocktail sauce over top.
Drain crabmeat and separate with a fork.
Sprinkle crabmeat over top of cocktail sauce.
Surround with crackers.

title: creamy shrimp shells
directions: Reserve 6 whole shrimp, cut remainder in half lengthwise and set aside.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in flour and salt, remove from heat and gradually add half and half, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Stir in wine and shrimp.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine everything except vanilla.
Cook until a soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat and whip a little.
Add vanilla and beat until it thickens.
Pour into buttered pan and let it cool until it hardens.
Cut into 2-inch squares for a real treat.

title: all american macaroni salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill at least 2 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or can spread on a baking pizza pan.
Bake as directed on package. Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and vanilla in bowl; mix well.
Spread over cool cookie dough.
Add fruit to top of pizza. Combine gelatine to fruit juices in a pan; bring to a boil.
Stir a lot because it will want to stick to bottom of pan.
Let set until slightly thick, then pour over pizza.
Chill a few hours before serving.
Refrigerate.

title: beef 'n tater pie
directions: In skillet, brown meat, carrots, mushrooms and onion.
Add soup to meat and mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange potatoes evenly over top.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake an additional 10 minutes. Serves 6.
Can be frozen.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Scoop out center of each roll with melon baller.
Set rolls aside.
Combine crabmeat and next 6 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon about 2 teaspoons crabmeat mixture into each roll.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
Garnish with ripe olives and parsley sprigs.
Yields 40 appetizers.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Fry bacon; drain and crumble. Set aside. Scoop flesh of potatoes into a large bowl. Add sour cream, milk, butter, salt and pepper, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 of green onion. Mix with mixer until well blended and creamy. Butter the bottom of a baking dish and spoon mixture in potato. Sprinkle with remaining cheese, green onions and bacon. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pot pie chicken
directions: Drain vegetables; add chicken and soup.
Mix well.
Pour in pie shell.
Add top pie shell and vent.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes until brown.

title: stir-fry
directions: Trim fat off stew meat and cut into desired size cubes.
Wash and drain vegetables.
Core cabbage and cut into quarters.
To cut vegetables, cut at an angle and rotate 1/4 turn.

title: green beans
directions: Drain beans; wash lightly.
Add enough water to cover beans. Cook on medium heat for about 20 minutes.
Add salt to taste.
May add a slice of fatback before cooking, if you wish.

title: golden granola
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
In microwave, cook at High about 8 minutes or until light golden brown, stirring every 2 minutes of cooking.
Stir in raisins.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet or aluminum foil to cool thoroughly.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: easy pizza
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Spoon beef into a 9-inch square pan.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine Bisquick, milk and eggs. Beat until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheeseburg pie(easy and delicious)
directions: Fry ground beef and onion with garlic clove; drain.
Add tomato sauce and herbs, salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Mix the chicken, all cheeses, onion, eggs, garlic powder and parsley.
Stuff mixture into uncooked noodles.
Mix 2 cans of soup with 2 cans of milk in separate bowl.
Mix until creamy.
Put noodles in a 9 x 13-inch glass or metal pan.
Pour soup mixture over noodles.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: steak and potato salad
directions: Place the steak in a shallow bowl and pour the marinade over it.
Let sit while preparing the potatoes.
Turn several times to coat the steak well.
Cook the potatoes in lightly salted water until fork tender.
Drain and set aside.

Remove the steak from the marinade and blot with paper towel to remove excess marinade. Cut into thin strips (similar to steak used in stir-fries). Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet. Saute the onions until tender but not browned.
Remove from pan.
Add remaining tablespoon of oil to pan.
Add the steak strips and cook until no longer pink.
Add onions back to pan along with the cooked potatoes.
Sprinkle with seasoning and mix lightly. Keep warm.
Combine the sour cream and mayonnaise in a small bowl.
Stir to mix.
Add to steak and potato mixture and gently stir.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve warm. Makes about 6 servings.

title: cheese biscuits #2
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. Mix and sift dry ingredients. Cut in the shortening and cheese. Add pecans and milk. Roll to 1/2-inch thickness and cut out, bake.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and salad oil together.
Add well beaten eggs; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in.
Mix until smooth. Add chopped walnuts and grated carrots.
Bake in 3 greased cake pans at 325° or Bundt cake pan about 30 minutes.
Oil and lightly flour Bundt pan.

title: chess pie
directions: Heat milk and butter on low heat until butter melts.
Beat eggs one at a time until well beaten.
Add sugar and flour and mix well with eggs.
Pour warm milk over sugar and egg mixture and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9-inch).
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients in large bowl; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: golden corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, beans, onions, cheese, soup and sour cream together.
Place in a casserole dish.
Mix topping of crackers, almonds and butter together.
Spread topping over the top of the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cheezy chili mexicana
directions: Combine ground chuck and onions in soup pot.
Cook until meat is no longer pink.
Drain excess grease.
Add chili seasoning, tomatoes, water and chili beans.
Cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Stir in cheese soup and continue cooking for another 5 to 10 minutes, adding more water, if needed.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Do not allow chili to boil once the sour cream has been added.
Enjoy with tortilla chips, crackers, or Mexican cornbread.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Place cornmeal in a large bowl.
Pour in boiling water gradually, stirring until no dry cornmeal is visible.
Let stand until cool.
Shape into balls; flatten slightly.
Fry in 1/4 inches hot oil in a cast-iron skillet until brown on both sides, turning once.
Serve with turnip greens or other vegetables.
May add additional boiling water for thinner batter consistency to drop from spoon into hot oil.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 10 to 12 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: russian black bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Combine rye and white flours.
In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 1/3 cups flour mixture, sugar, salt, cereal, caraway seed, instant coffee, onion powder, fennel seed and undissolved dry yeast.

title: kaye's ham balls
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, milk and eggs and form into balls. Put into casserole dish.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a buttered casserole dish.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups hot water. Cool. Add pineapple, marshmallows and bananas. Chill in a large flat dish until firm. Add flour and sugar to beaten egg.
Mix with juice from pineapple and cook until thick over medium heat, stirring constantly. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over gelatin. Sprinkle cheese and nuts over all. Cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: bran buttermilk muffins(diabetic recipe)
directions: Mix together and bake at 400 for 20 minutes.

title: cameo no-bake fruitcakes
directions: Combine marshmallows, evaporated milk and orange juice in a small bowl.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and spices; mix well. Stir in coconut, fruits and nuts.
Add liquid mixture.
Press together until moist and sticky.

title: bacon dogs
directions: Cut wieners into 4 pieces.
Wrap bacon around wiener and hold together with wooden toothpick.
Put half of wieners into crock-pot.
Add 1 pound of brown sugar.
Use rest of wieners, then brown sugar.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then 2 1/2 to 3 hours on low, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Pour all the mixture into a large buttered casserole (large Pyrex glass), 11 x 14-inch, and top with sharp grated cheese. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, dressing and vanilla with mixer on medium speed.
Add flour and baking soda.
Set aside 1 cup of the batter.
Spread remaining batter into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 10 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk in heavy saucepan on low heat, stirring frequently until smooth.
Top crust with caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with chips and pecans.
Spoon reserved 1 cup batter by teaspoon over pecans.
Continue baking 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pear pecan salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and reserve 1 cup of liquid.
Bring juice to a boil.
Remove from heat and add lemon jello.
Chill in a 9 x 13-inch pan until partially set.
Blend pears and cream cheese until of creamy consistency.
Stir in jello mixture.
Add pecans.
Whip cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into mold or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown ground beef and add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms and pepperoni to heat.
Mix together with noodles and place in casserole dish.
Put cheese slices on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine Russian dressing, dry onion soup mix and preserves. Pour over chicken parts which have been placed in a single layer, skin side up, in large shallow baking dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, basting occasionally with the pan drippings.
Serve hot with plain rice and the sweet and sour sauce.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Mix cheese, soup, catsup and milk.
Add to beef and onion.
Pour into casserole.
Put biscuits on top of mixture before baking at 350° until biscuits are done.
A 10-inch casserole dish or skillet works fine for baking.

title: cranberry apple ice(low calorie)
directions: In 2 qt. glass bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover - Freeze until firm.
Scoop frozen mixture into 5 oz. drink cups, or spoon into dessert dishes.
Makes 14 - 1/2 cup servings - 1 Point.

title: apple chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix together first seven ingredients.
Fold in apples, chocolate and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix crackers, margarine and 1/2 c. sugar together and press into 9 X 13 pan. Beat eggs, 3/4 cup sugar, and cream cheese together and pour over graham cracker crust. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: fruit cocktail torte
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Very moist cake.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cut chicken into cubes. Put in large skillet with butter. Cook a few minutes until chicken is white. Add chopped pepper and minced garlic. Heat 4 or 5 minutes until all is hot. Add salsa. Remove from fire. Tear tortillas in pieces. Layer with chicken mix and cheeses in baking dish. Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. This freezes well.

directions: With mixer
cream margarine and sugar; add one egg at a time, beating
after

egg.

soda and stir, then add alternately
flour

Mix

Mix well.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Bake in slow oven at 300°, 1 hour and 45 minutes.
While
cake
is in oven mix together 1 cup undiluted orange juice
1/2 cans), 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar and set aside.
Test
cake with toothpick after 1 hour and 45 minutes. As soon

Pour

24 hours
out
of refrigerator, then take out of pan. Will
last covered with Saran Wrap out of refrigerator several months.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Ingredients will be layered into an 8 X 9 inch square casserole dish.
Season hamburger meat as desired and spread on the bottom of your casserole dish.
Pour mushroom soup over hamburger and spread evenly.
Cut cheese into slices approximately 1/4 inch thick and place each slice neatly over the soup until it is all covered.
Take approximately 3/4 bag of tater tots and layer over cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees and enjoy.

title: overnight layered salad
directions: Wash and dry lettuce and spinach and break into bite size pieces.
Place in large bowl.
Top with celery, onion, peas and radishes.
Sprinkle lightly with salt, pepper, sugar and Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat the oven to 350°.

Beat the shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy. Add the combined dry ingredients and mix well. Drop by rounded spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 12 to 15 minutes. Cool on a wire rack and cool completely. Store tightly covered.

title: final exam brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs and beat.
Add remaining ingredients, except 1/2 cup chips.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chips on top. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: jello peach pie
directions: Mix into a ball.
Press in a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil
cabbage
in
salted
water
for
8 to 10 minutes. Drain. Lay
wedges in buttered baking dish.
Cut out core and discard. Salt
and pepper to taste.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Mix soup
with milk; pour over cheese and cabbage.
Add butter or oleo.
Bake
at 350° for 40 minutes.
Add buttered crumbs last 10 minutes.

title: ham with sauced potatoes and salad
directions: Boil, peel and slice in crosswise 1/3 pieces.
Marinate potato slices in following mixture in refrigerator overnight.
Drain potato slices.
On plate, arrange potatoes on lettuce leaf.
Add tomato slices, egg slices, onion and ham.
Top with following sauce.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together egg, sugar, milk, raisins, caraway seed and Crisco.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Layer in microwave safe bowl (large).
Cook on High 3 minutes with bowl covered with paper towel.
Whip with mixer until blended. Pour into buttered dish.
Let cool.
Store covered in refrigerator. May add 3/4 cup peanut butter, nuts, raisins, etc. after microwave.

title: terry's bean soup
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and garlic in 3 tablespoons of oil. Dilute bean and bacon soup to desired consistency.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 2 hours on low.
Add smoked sausage, if desired.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, salt and milk in saucepan.
Place over heat and bring mixture to a hard boil.
Let boil one minute. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper or spread evenly in long shallow pan.
Let stand until firm and cool.

title: cod a la spetse
directions: Brush 1 tablespoon of oil in the bottom of a shallow baking dish large enough to accommodate the fish in one layer with space in between.
Mix remaining oil with wine, parsley, lemon juice, garlic, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle diced tomato over fish and pour on the oil-wine mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until fish flakes when probed with a fork.

title: pea casserole
directions: Mix and pour in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 package cornbread stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine
oil and sugar; mix well.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together; add
to
mixture
half at a time.
Beat well, about 5 or 10 minutes.
Add
apples, nuts and flavoring; mix well.
Bake in 9 x 14-inch
pan
at
325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese, egg and sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs with mustard, milk, salt and butter.
Make 2 layers: bread, sausage and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour egg mixture over top. Put some shredded cheese on top.
Use a greased 9-inch square pan or something similar.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 6.
This should be made the night before so it can soak.
Can be frozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and spices.
Add apples, nuts and raisins; beat well.
Pour into a large round cake pan (Bundt pan) which has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer this over the stuffing mix.

title: fantastic pot roast and dumplings
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven over high heat.
Add onion and brown slightly.
Add meat and brown well.
Pour undiluted consomme over meat and sprinkle with bay leaf, orange peel, salt, allspice and pepper.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 3 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove meat to a warm platter and cover with foil to keep warm.
Stir Bisquick and milk together.
Add water to the liquid in the pan.
Drop Bisquick mixture into the pan liquid by large tablespoonfuls.
Cook over low heat uncovered for 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes longer.
Don't peek! Serve immediately.
Freezes well.
Serves 6.

title: cajun crab dip
directions: Very finely chop crabmeat.
Place meat in bowl first.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: rich crumbly peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar and sugar.
Beat butter, then add sugar gradually, until creamy.
Beat in egg, peanut butter, salt and soda.
Carefully measure flour.
Add to batter, then add vanilla and carob chips.
Roll dough in small balls.
Put on greased tin.
Press flat with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stew chicken until tender.
Do not add salt, but other seasoning can be added.
Save the chicken broth. Pick meat off chicken, making sure pieces are cubed or sliced, and set aside.
In bowl, mix dressing with melted butter and set aside. In another bowl, dilute can of soup with can of broth and set aside.
In a greased casserole dish add a layer of dressing mixture followed by a layer of chicken (about 1/2 of chicken), and pour approximately 3/4 can of plain chicken broth over chicken.
Don't overly moisten first layer.
Repeat the dressing layer, remainder of chicken and remainder of soup/broth mixture.
Top with remainder of dressing mix.
Cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown.

title: thick-n-rich hot fudge topping
directions: In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes or until mixture is slightly thickened.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Boil puddings, jello and water for 2 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mixture.
Stir in desired fruit.

title: pumpkin pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Boil pared pumpkin in salt water until soft.
Drain well, put through food mill to make pulp.
In large bowl, combine pumpkin, milk and beaten eggs.
Stir well.
Mix together sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon then add to pumpkin.
Lastly, slightly brown butter and stir into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into pie crusts and bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 375° until done, about 50 minutes (or until knife comes out clean).
(Secret:
Use fresh pumpkin.)

title: lemon cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Whip until ice cream is well blended.
Serve immediately.
Makes eight 8-ounce servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in pan; add all soups and water.
Spread rice in bottom of ungreased (13 x 9-inch) baking dish.
Pour a bit more than 1/2 the soup over rice and mix well.
Put breasts on top, then remainder of soup sauce.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours, uncovered.
Serves 6.
(Nine or ten breasts can be used.)

title: egg custard
directions: Combine all ingredients together and beat well. Pour into precooked pie shell. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Put a dash of nutmeg on top of filling.
You can use any flavoring you like.
I look at the pie and judge if it has cooked until firm.

title: tomato marmalade
directions: Peel, chop and drain tomatoes.
Add lemon, sliced paper thin. Add sugar.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add Jell-O and stir.
Put into jars.

title: onion cheese bake
directions: Brown onion slices slightly in the butter.
Spread in baking dish and top with the sliced eggs, then sprinkle cheese on top. Mix cream of mushroom soup with the evaporated milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over casserole and punch holes.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Brown at 350°.

title: chicken and rice soup
directions: Wash and cover chicken with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth to cool, reserving broth.
Add celery and onion to broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until vegetables are tender.
Wash rice until most of the starch is removed.
Cover rice with water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Cover and remove from heat.
Do not remove lid for 15 minutes or until rice has absorbed all the water.
Gradually add rice to broth.
Skin and debone chicken, leaving in large pieces. Add chicken to broth and rice.
Add tomatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Heat to serve.
Serve with hot cornbread.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Combine sour cream and lemon juice in a bowl.

Stir in grapes, mandarins, chicken, celery and 2 tablespoons of the coconut. Arrange lettuce leaves on four individual plates, spoon on chicken mixture, garnish with remaining coconut and carrot sticks.
Serves 4.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer lettuce pieces, peas, chestnuts, onion and cheese. After all is layered, cover with mayonnaise.
Cover and put in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.
Mix and serve.

title: easy dorm tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Place in casserole and mix in cream of mushroom soup and tuna (and sliced mushrooms, if desired).
Can place shredded cheese on top and heat in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Layer meat mixture as first layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, then layer in following order: beans, tortillas, Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, Ro-Tel tomato juice, mushroom soup (undiluted).
Top with chopped Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix sour cream and soup.
Combine melted butter, cracker crumbs, and poppy seeds.
Place in baking dish and cover with soup mixture.
Place cracker mixture on top and cook at 350 degree for 30 minutes or until bubbly!

title: cheesy-sausage dip
directions: Crumble and cook sausage; drain.
Combine cooked sausage, cheese and tomatoes in crock-pot.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: lime punch
directions: Dissolve 4 cups of hot water, 2 pkg. of lime gelatin and 1 cup of sugar and let stand.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix pudding, pineapple and juice together. Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan and chill overnight.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Use medium cookie sheet and line with foil, then butter the foil.
Line with the soda crackers.
In a small pan, put butter and brown sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture over the soda crackers.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chocolate chips.
After they melt, spread with knife and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: cherry squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup oats.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg; mix until well blended.
Press into pan.
Pour pie filling in and spread to cover.
To reserved crumbs, in large bowl, add remaining 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts and brown sugar.
Beat until well mixed.
Sprinkle over cherry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown. Cool completely.
If desired, serve with whipped cream.
Serves 12.

title: arlie r's pie crust(3 pies)
directions: Combine ice water with vinegar; stir in beaten egg and set aside.
Work shortening into flour mixture (all dry ingredients). Make well in flour mix; sprinkle water mix over all.
Gently toss to form dough (2 forks do well).
Shape into balls, according to how many crusts are needed (3 balls or less.)
Cover tightly (self seal plastic bags work well).
Chill several hours or freeze up to 6 months.
Good crust for any recipe.

title: chuck wagon bean casserole
directions: Saute hamburger until brown and separated.
Drain off excess fat.
Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Stir well, taking care not to mash beans.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: crusty crab points
directions: When using canned crabmeat, drain.
Combine all ingredients, except muffins, with electric mixer.
Spread on English muffin halves.
Freeze for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cut each muffin half into 6 wedges.
Re-freeze in plastic bags until ready to serve.
Broil until golden brown and bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Filling is also good on party rye or leave muffin halves uncut and serve as open-face sandwich.

title: liz's strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cheese and vanilla until creamy. Add Cool Whip and sprinkle jello over it and blend well. Drain juice from berries and fold in. Pour into crusts. Cool for at least 2 hours before serving.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or 3 graham cracker pies.

title: crusty meat loaf
directions: Thaw bread dough in refrigerator overnight.
Cover.
Let stand on floured surface at room temperature for 1 hour.
Save 1 tablespoon egg for glaze.
Combine remainder of eggs and remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Shape meat mixture into a 9 x 4-inch loaf and place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Drain.
Press dough onto bottom of greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Place meat loaf in center of dough. Fold dough ends over loaf. Brush with reserved egg. Bake at 350° until bread dough browns.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add chopped peppers, corn, cheese and salt; mix well.
Sift together the flour, cornmeal and baking powder.
Add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured oblong cake pan (9 x 13 x 3-inch).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Reduce heat to 300°.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: delicate lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir flour and sugar with a fork until blended.
Cut in butter until mixture hangs together.
Pat into an ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
May prepare ahead.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Bake shell 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Melt chocolate chips with oleo, mixing well.
Add Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla, blending well.
Mix in biscuit mix. Fold in nuts.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake about 35 to 45 minutes, until set.

title: holiday potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in water 15 minutes until tender; drain and mash.
Add butter and cream cheese.
Beat at medium speed on mixer until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup Cheddar and next 6 ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 baking dish.
Cover and chill, if desired.
Remove casserole from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Cheddar.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
May be baked without chilling.
Baking time may be less than 40 minutes.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Slowly add to the dry ingredients the oil, egg and buttermilk; mix well.
Add blueberries.
Cook in greased pan until lightly brown.
Turn once.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Wash and drain mushrooms.
Mix together all ingredients.
Add mushrooms and let sit overnight.
(Minimum time 8 hours).
Shake or stir once in awhile.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; chill 3 or 4 hours.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot (360°) oil.
Cook until golden brown.
Serve hot with butter, barbecue and other things that you enjoy hush puppies with.

title: party punch
directions: In pitcher, combine all ingredients.
Stir to dissolve sugar. Serve over ice.

title: gladys clark's fruit cake(this fruit cake contains no citrus fruit.)
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Cream in the butter or margarine and lemon juice.
Bring 2 cups water to a boil.
Add the raisins and chopped dried fruit; again bring to a boil.
Pour off water; drain fruit on paper towel and set aside.
Mix the nuts, dates, cherries and pineapple wedges in a large bowl.
Add dry ingredients to mixture in bowl; mix lightly until fruit and nuts are well coated.
(Can add the coconut, if desired.)

title: angie's chocolate eclair pie
directions: Mix milk with pudding.
Beat for about 3 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and beat for about 2 more minutes.
Layer graham crackers and pudding (usually put pudding first).
Last layer needs to be the graham crackers.
Spread chocolate icing over top. Refrigerate.
The longer it can refrigerate, the better.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar and oil.
Take out 1/2 cup for crumbs.
Mix remainder of crumbs with molasses, egg, hot water and baking soda.
Pour into crust.
Add 1/2 cup crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: cold spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti until done; drain, rinse and let set until cold.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients. Stir in Mazola oil and milk. Drop small tablespoon onto boiling stew. Cover and boil gently for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: super sausage bites
directions: Combine biscuit mix, cheese and sausage; blend well.
Roll sausage mixture into small balls.
Place on baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes or until browned.
Serve hot.
Yields 20 servings.

title: wesson's famous fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275° very slowly. Combine Wesson oil, brown sugar and eggs. Beat vigorously with spoon or electric mixer for 2 minutes. Sift 2 cups of the flour with the baking powder, salt and spices. Stir into the oil mixture alternately with the fruit juice. Mix the other cup of flour with the fruits and nuts. Pour batter over the fruit, mixing thoroughly. Turn into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans or one Bundt cake pan. Grease pans and line with brown paper. Place pan of water on the lower rack. Bake cake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. After baking, allow cake to cool in the pan. Wrap and refrigerate. Enjoy.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown meat; add salt, pepper, garlic salt, chili powder (optional) and onion.
Add tomato sauce and cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Slightly grease skillet and warm tortilla shells on each side.
Place small amount of meat and cheese on each shell and roll up.
Place on cookie sheet; then sprinkle remainder cheese over enchiladas and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix can of Mexican sauce and green peppers to make sauce; pour over enchiladas when done.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, beat butter, water, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until lightly brown.
Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: fruitcake
directions: After mixing these ingredients, add the fruit. Bake in greased and floured Bundt pans at 300° until done. Test with toothpick. Cool completely. Decorate with sliced candied pineapple and cherries.

title: chicken tenders
directions: Cut up chicken breasts.
Dip in milk and egg.
Roll in crushed potato chips with onion salt and pepper.
Set at room temperature for 5 minutes.
Top with butter.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fish stew
directions: Fry bacon.
Remove from pan.
Brown onions in drippings. Place 3 c. water in large pot.
Bring to boil.
Pour onion and drippings into pot.
Add fish, Tabasco, Worcestershire and salt and pepper.
Cook until fish is done.
Add ketchup and tomato paste.
Cook 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add salt, garlic, Italian seasoning, basil and sugar.
Add tomato sauce; simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, egg and chives until creamy.
Layer in pan with noodles, then creamy mixture, then hamburger mixture.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line 11
x
18-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Cover with graham crackers,
side by side.
Put brown sugar and butter in pan and boil for 4 minutes.
Pour mixture over graham crackers and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend milk and Cool Whip well, then add other ingredients.
Buy ready-made graham cracker crusts (use two).
Pour pie filling in crusts and chill.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Stir together sour cream and soda.
Put to side.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat in sour cream and soda mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients until just blended.
Do not overmix.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: limeade
directions: Add all ingredients and mix.
Then chill in refrigerator.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt
margarine, sugar and milk and boil for 8 minutes. Set aside
and	add
chocolate	nuggets and Hip-O-Lite.
Beat until smooth, then add nuts.
Pour in greased Pyrex dish.

title: raspberry cornmeal muffins
directions: Gently rinse berries; pat dry and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine eggs, milk and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine flour, sugar, cornmeal, baking powder, salt and grated orange peel.
Stir egg-milk mixture into the flour mixture, along with the melted butter.
(Stir just enough to blend ingredients; do not overmix.)

title: stuffed burger balls
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to directions on box.
Mix milk and ground beef and divide into 4 to 6 patties.
In center of each patty, put 1/4 cup stuffing and mold meat around stuffing to form a ball.
Place on 8 x 8-inch pan and pour soup over meat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baste several times.
Serve with vegetables, potatoes and salad.
Use soup sauce as a gravy.

title: parmesan zucchini
directions: Wash and slice squash.
Put in medium sized saucepan and add bouillon, minced onion, celery, tomato puree and more salt and some pepper if needed to taste.
Put on to cook, covered, over low heat, being careful to check to see that the moisture is enough. A very little water may be added.
When it begins to tender, add the Italian seasoning; pour into casserole and set in medium oven. Allow to bake for 40 minutes to an hour.
When ready to serve, serve with Parmesan cheese grated over top.
This has a definite pizza like flavor.
This is a weight controlling recipe, but don't tell your family!

title: coconut buttermilk cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add flour and buttermilk, then add other ingredients, mixing with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in a well-greased and floured pan.

title: traditional sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients and simmer until desired consistency.

title: jordana's coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, vegetable oil, milk and egg with an electric mixer.
Pour batter into well-greased 9-inch round cake pan.

title: baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken parts, skin side up, in dry roast pan.
Roll loose skin under each piece.
Place a thin pat of butter on each piece and salt and pepper generously.
Bake for 1 hour, reversing pan after first half hour.
Baste several times during baking with juice which accumulates.
Juice may be used for gravy.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Place fryer in large pot. Cover halfway with water and boil until tender. Remove fryer and debone. Break dumplings into thirds and drop into boiling stock. (If stock is not boiling, rolling, the dumplings will stick together.) Add salt, pepper and poultry seasoning to taste. Lower heat and stir often to prevent sticking. If you need more liquid, add canned chicken broth, cream of chicken soup or maybe a little milk. Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes. Add boned chicken to dumplings. Simmer a few minutes and serve. This is yummy!

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix pudding according to
package directions.
Chill.
In large mixing bowl, mix jello and boiling water.
Stir well until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries.
Stir and mix well until strawberries are defrosted.
Add pudding, stir well.
Add sliced bananas.
Break cake into small pieces and add to jello mixture, pushing down until covered.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, 1 small onion and taco seasoning.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan or on two plates.
Top with taco sauce.
Layer remaining ingredients on top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered sugar together.
Put half of the mixture in a cooled baked pie shell.
Put the other half of the mixture in the prepared vanilla pudding and pour it in the pie shell.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place shrimp in boiling salted water. Add bay leaf, pickle spice, cayenne pepper, garlic and lemon. Boil for 10 minutes or until shells turn pink. Remove shrimp; peel and remove veins. Cool. Grind shrimp with onions. Add celery and enough mayonnaise to hold mixture together. Serve with potato chips or snack crackers.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Spread pecans and coconut in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as package directs and pour over pecans and coconut. Melt together oleo and cream cheese.
Add confectioners sugar and mix well; pour on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: low calorie onion dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine yogurt and cottage cheese until well blended.
Stir in soup mix and chili powder.
Refrigerate 3 hours or longer to let flavor develop.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and let stand overnight.
Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Add orange juice, celery, pineapple, orange rind and cranberries.
Chill.

title: pizza meat loaves
directions: Combine meat, bread, 1/2 cup cheese and mushrooms.
Mix lightly.
Shape mixture in 4 small loaves; place in shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brush with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Continue baking 10 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in oven.
When done, slice in half longways.
Be careful not to tear peeling.
Scoop out the potatoes into a medium bowl.
Add salt, pepper and butter; mix with beater on medium speed.
Add milk and beat again for 1 minute.
Scoop potatoes back into peelings and top with cheese.
Bake again until cheese is melted.

title: pressed chicken
directions: Cut up chicken in the usual manner and place in a kettle with a tight lid so as to retain the steam; put water, salt and pepper over chicken, then cook.
Cut up meat freed from skin.
Put in dish and pour juice over meat.
this will gel and can be sliced when cold.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine beef, onion, toast, ketchup and egg. Form into a loaf and place in pan.

title: a very special jell-o dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water, stir until dissolved, add cold water and stir thoroughly. Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Put broth in saucepan you cooked the onion and celery in.
Add chopped liver and gizzard and boil for about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. In a small glass, place flour and then add water. Stir until well mixed and all lumps have been dissolved.
Add to broth mixture and return to heat. Cook until thick. Remove from heat. Add chopped eggs and food coloring.
Stir well. Serve over dressing.

title: tahiti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Cover tightly and chill overnight.

title: persimmon steamed "pudding"
directions: In large bowl, combine persimmon pulp, sugar and butter.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to fruit mixture alternately with the milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Any or all of the raisins, walnuts and candied lemon peel are optional.
Grease and flour a deep baking pan.
(My mother used a 1 pound coffee can.)
Pour batter into pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Place pan into a shallow pan of hot water.)

title: boston baked beans(microwave)
directions: Remove and discard any stones from beans; rinse and drain. In a 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine beans and 6 cups water.
In microwave, cook covered on High 16 to 22 minutes, until boiling. Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Remove and let stand covered 1 hour. Cook covered at Medium (50% power) 30 to 40 minutes, until beans are tender, but not soft.
Press cloves into onion; add with remaining ingredients to casserole.
Cook covered on High 30 to 40 minutes, stirring 4 times until beans are soft.
If desired, remove and discard onion before serving.
Makes 12 serving (1/2 cup); 262 calories, 10 g protein, 9 g fat, 37 g carbohydrates and 197 mg sodium.

title: world's easiest, fastest & bestest best fudge
directions: Mix the
milk, sugar and salt in a saucepan and heat to boiling; continue to cook for 5 minutes over medium-high heat, stirring
constantly.
Remove
from heat and add marshmallows; stir
until
mixed.
Add
chocolate and continue to stir until well
mixed
and
marshmallows
and chocolate are melted.
Add vanilla
and
nuts; mix.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan and cool
for 20 minutes.
(Preparation time:
15 minutes plus 20 minutes.)

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into partially baked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven temperature to 325° and bake 50 minutes.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup; bring just to a boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter; melt together. Mix in Rice Krispies. Press into a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan.

title: top o' the stove cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa and boil 3 minutes.
Add salt, vanilla and oats.
Cool slightly.
Add walnuts and/or coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: english pea dish
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Pour all ingredients in and top with 2 tablespoons of butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mother's brown bread(mors grovbrod)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water; let stand for 15 minutes.
In a large bowl, add 3 1/2 cups lukewarm water, molasses, salt, sugar and shortening.
Add enough flour to make a soft sponge.
Beat thoroughly.
Add remainder of flour to make stiff dough.
Knead dough well.
May add some shortening to kneading surface to help kneading.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place.
When double in bulk, knead again.
Let rise once more, then shape into 4 loaves.
Place in loaf pans.
Let dough rise until loaves are double in size.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir over medium heat until smooth and bubbly.
Stir in cooked broccoli; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir in half and half and milk, heat to serving temperature.
Serve with dab of sour cream, yogurt or grated Cheddar cheese on top.

title: orange-cream brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line a 9-inch round baking pan with foil; grease and set aside.
In bowl with mixer at high beat cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Beat in 1 egg, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon flour and orange peel; set aside.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix ingredients together well in large bowl. Add wings and marinate overnight. Place wings on baking sheet with some of the marinade and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer, turning occasionally.

title: chess cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Melt
margarine in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour
cake
mix
over melted margarine.
Add 1 egg, mix well. (I
use
my
hands and work up like dough.) Pat over bottom and
sides
like pie crust.
Mix softened cream cheese, powdered sugar.
Add
eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
tags: golden recipe butter yellow cake mix

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until top is brown, in a layer pan or pie plate.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, combine broth, water and potatoes.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add vegetables, tomatoes, beef, thyme and pepper.
Cover; heat to simmering.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown meat in a large skillet, drain well.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles according to package directions, using 1 teaspoon each of oil and salt; drain.
Layer half of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, then repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix vegetables and salt.
Let stand overnight.
Wash well in colander.
Put in a large pan.

title: pancake mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir to blend well. Put in airtight container.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place. Use within 6 to 8 months.
Makes about 13 cups pancake mix.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: In a 2-cup glass measuring cup, combine water and margarine. Microwave on High 2 minutes or until water is boiling and margarine is melted.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well; pour mixture in blender jar and whirl until smooth.
Makes the equivalent of 1 can of sweetened condensed milk and can be used in any recipe calling for sweetened condensed milk.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 10 x 14-inch cake pan.
Spread coconut and pecans in the bottom of the pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed. Pour batter over coconut and pecans.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove cake from oven and cool 10 minutes.
Combine margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over warm cake.

title: apple smothered pork chops
directions: Season chops with salt, pepper and sage. Brown in small amount of oil.
Remove from skillet.
Stir flour into skillet.
Stir in water, vinegar and raisins. Arrange chops in casserole top with apple slices.
Pour molasses over apples and add flour mixture. Bake covered for 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pennsylvania dutch style chicken and corn soup
directions: Cook chicken in water slowly until it is tender, adding salt 30 minutes before it is done.
Remove chicken and strain broth through a fine sieve.
Take meat from bones and cut in bite size pieces. Set aside.
Add corn to broth.
Add onion, chopped celery and seasoning; cook 5 minutes.
Five minutes before serving, add chicken, diced eggs and rivels.

title: coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, or until light brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip; blend together.
Use a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Alternate pudding mixture with whole graham crackers, beginning and ending with crackers.
Top with icing.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, grapes, celery, sugar and mayo. Add salt and pepper to taste. Cover salad and chill at least an hour. Serve on lettuce leaves and top with slivered almonds.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into dish or cupcake holders and freeze.
May be refrozen.
Serves about 24.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with chicken breasts.
Cover chicken with a layer of Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and water.
Pour over cheese.
Melt oleo and mix stuffing mix.
Sprinkle on top of soup layer. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together; add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream and milk; mix well.
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Yields one 10-inch cake.

title: lime freeze
directions: Mix the limeade and ginger ale. Add the lime sherbet and beat until smooth.
Pour into tall glasses and garnish each serving with an additional scoop of sherbet.

title: dip
directions: Mix all together in blender.
Serve with raw vegetables and baked potato.

title: blueberry scones
directions: Heat oven to 400°, rack in center of oven.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press 1 roll of cookie dough in bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Put on top of cookie dough.
Press other roll of dough and put on top. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a mixing bowl. Beat with a mixer on high setting for a minute.

title: farmers casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper. Brown meat and drain. Mix with vegetables.
Add rest of ingredients except biscuits. Put in casserole.
Place biscuits on top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kentucky spoon bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza baked fish
directions: For sauce, in a small saucepan, combine half of the mushrooms, onion, water, tomato paste, basil, oregano, sugar, fennel seed, red pepper and garlic.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 4 minutes, stirring the mixture occasionally.
Remove from heat.

title: turkey broccoli divan
directions: Cook broccoli
to
crisp-tender; drain and place spears in an 11 x 7 x 1-inch baking dish with tips pointing out.
Top with turkey slices.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over turkey.
Top with cheese slices.
Bake at 350° for
to
minutes.
Sprinkle
with onion rings. Bake 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and rinse well with cold water.
Add celery, green peppers, tomatoes and drained olives.
Mix well with Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.

title: hong kong pork chops
directions: Season chops; brown in oil.
Cover with onion slices.
Combine soy sauce, sherry, lemon juice, mushrooms, ginger and garlic powder.
Pour over chops.
Bake, covered, for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, 15 more minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: warm fruit compote
directions: In chafing dish or large saucepan, combine margarine, sugar, cornstarch, orange rind, orange juice and lemon juice.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until slightly thickened.
Stir in fruit.
Simmer just until fruit is warm.
Serve warm.

title: mountain stew
directions: Stew meat until tender.
Remove from bones.
Add vegetables to meat and seasonings.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Add butter and breadcrumbs to thicken.
Serve hot with cornbread.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and place in buttered baking dish.

title: taco salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces; mix with beans, onion, tomatoes and corn chips.
Add Catalina just before serving.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken.
Saute vegetables until soft (not mushy).
Add soup, chicken and pepper.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Meanwhile cook noodles as directed on package. Serve chicken over noodles.

title: super spice cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift other dry ingredients, then add alternately the buttermilk and dry ingredients to the shortening mixture.
Beat about 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Place all ingredients in electric blender at low speed for 1 minute.
Pour into china pots or small custard cups.
Chill several hours.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Set cream cheese out to room temperature, then beat in mixing bowl. Cut ham fine. Pour onions and ham in cream cheese and mix well. Roll in medium balls.
Roll in pecan meal. Serve with any kind of snack crackers.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Put flour and seasoning in large bag.
Coat all chicken pieces. In a large baking pan, melt 2 tablespoons margarine and 2 tablespoons of Wesson or Crisco oil.
Put chicken in pan and bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Turn chicken over and bake 30 more minutes.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cover chicken with water in large pot and boil until done. Remove from bone and cut in bite size chunks.
Crumble cornbread and wheat bread together.
Add other ingredients to bread mixture including the chicken.
Mix all of this together using the broth from cooking the chicken.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Combine cream cheese and salsa.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll up.
Chill 1 hour or more.
Slice into pinwheels and serve.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour peaches on top of melted butter.
Mix together Bisquick and sugar. Add milk and stir until the mixture is the consistency of pancake batter.
Pour this mixture on top of the peaches. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: milky way cake
directions: Mix together candy bars and oleo.
Melt and set aside.
Mix sugar and shortening; dissolve soda in hot water.
Add to buttermilk, eggs, cake flour, nuts and vanilla.
Mix all together well and add to melted Milky Way mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add frosting.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, gradually.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Mix milk and macaroni water.
Add to roux, slowly.
Stir until it boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese (mix grated and Cheddar).
Save some cheese to spread on top.
Mix sauce with macaroni.
Sprinkle cheese on top and add a few thin slices of butter.
Bake at 375° until brown and crisp on top.

title: upside-down mince gingerbread
directions: Combine mincemeat, 1/4 cup melted butter and 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Place in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: frito casserole
directions: Saute onion in Wesson oil.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and tomato ketchup.
Saute ground beef in skillet and salt; add to mixture.
Line casserole with Fritos; add beef mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: night-before french toast
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in small pan and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay bread in mixture.
Combine eggs, milk and cinnamon; pour over pieces of bread.
Cover and set in refrigerator overnight.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: tater bake
directions: Thaw Tater Tots, crumble about 2/3 of bag into greased 10 x 14-inch Pyrex.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Put 1/2 of egg mixture (or 1 carton) evenly on top.
Lay Velveeta slices over top. Crumble rest of Tater Tots on top, salt and pepper.
Pour rest of egg mixture (or second carton of egg substitute) on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown ground beef. Drain. Line bottom of large casserole dish with crunched Doritos. Add an even amount of all other ingredients in layer: the ground beef, picante sauce, 1/2 can cream of mushroom, 1/2 can cream of chicken, 1/2 can sour cream and 1/2 package shredded cheeses. Repeat layers, starting with Doritos. Bake in a 350° oven until cheeses are bubbling, approximately 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Beat at low speed until light.
Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
If necessary, add milk to make spreading consistency.
Stir in chopped nuts, if desired.
Frosts 1 (8 or 9-inch) cake.

title: none left green beans
directions: Cook bacon.
Drain and set aside.
Chop onions and saute in small amount of bacon grease.
Add green beans and crumble bacon on top.
Cook on low heat 10 minutes.

title: ray's eggplant fritters
directions: Mix eggplant, potato, meat choice and egg.
Mix other ingredients thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Either make small patties or spoon into skillet of medium-hot grease. Brown to suit.
Eggplant may be used raw if tender and may be left out.
Relax and enjoy!

title: pineapple punch
directions: Mix all together in punch bowl, stirring well.
Refrigerate until chilled or serve over ice.

title: mock crab cakes(never near water or ocean)
directions: Mix all together and form into patties or use tablespoon to drop off in skillet with a little oil.
Brown and turn over.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Remove leaves from cabbage. Boil leaves until they are limp. Mix ground meat, rice, onion, garlic, bell pepper and eggs.
Roll in cabbage leaf. Secure with a toothpick.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce over rolls and lay bacon on top.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix corn muffin mix and pour half in a large iron skillet that has been greased.
Layer ground beef, cheese and corn.
Top with leftover corn muffin mix.
Bake at 375° until cornbread is done.

title: squash pie
directions: Pour in crust and cook until done.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries, leaving berries whole.
If berries are not especially ripe then it may be best to cut them.
Mix sugar, strawberry gelatin, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan.
Stir in boiling water.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring constantly. Boil 3 minutes.
Cool completely.
Arrange whole strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour glaze over berries.
Chill several hours. Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Save egg whites for meringue.

title: steak with green peppercorns
directions: *The canned variety, packed in brine, from Madagascar is best.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine and cover.
Place in cold oven and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana-chip bars
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in banana.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and beat well.
Stir in chocolate pieces.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool whip.
Spread on cool baked crust. Mix pudding with milk.
Spread on the mixture and add remaining Cool Whip to the top.
Chill well.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Cook cranberries in 2 quarts water until done.
Strain and save juice.
Add orange and lemon juice, red hots and sugar to juice and simmer until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cool and store in refrigerator.
When ready to use, add enough water to make a gallon.
Heat and serve.

title: zucchini saute
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Saute the zucchini and onions until tender.
Add the last 4 ingredients, cover and saute for 5 more minutes.

title: ground beef hash
directions: Brown beef and drain. Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 30 minutes. Add onions and Worcestershire sauce. Uncover and continue cooking for 15 minutes or until thick as desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper; drain.
Add garlic salt.
Line casserole dish with Tater Tots.
Pour in beef mixture.
Add 2 cans soup over Tater Tots.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 2 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Layer in order: chicken, broccoli, cheese and cream of celery soup.

title: hearty oatmeal muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups or line with baking cups.
Combine pancake mix, oats, brown sugar and cinnamon; add remaining ingredients until moistened. Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: hazie's vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in large boiler.
Cook on medium until vegetables are tender.

title: wayne newton's teriyaki
directions: Cut beef into strips, 1 x 2 inches long.
Combine rest of ingredients for marinade.
Marinate meat in tightly covered container 5 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
String beef on metal skewers; grill teriyaki on habachi 3 minutes or until meat is tender but rare, turning once.
Garnish with tiny cucumbers marinated in vinegar and soy sauce.
Serves 6.

title: country chicken pot pie
directions: Cut cooked chicken into cubes and place in large buttered casserole.
Add mushrooms, celery, onion, parsley, pepper and any other vegetables; mix in.

title: ooey-gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: breakfast pockets
directions: While the French toast is still frozen, insert a sharp knife into one side of each slice and cut a pocket, being careful not to cut through remaining 3 sides.
Let bread thaw at room temperature.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix ingredients in the order listed.
Do not overbeat.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in Bundt pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, butter, pecans, salt and vanilla.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until pie is done.

title: italian pasta bake
directions: Brown meat and drain; stir in noodles, spaghetti sauce, Italian cheese and 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Spoon in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: nancy's orange stuff
directions: Blend together the whipped topping and sour cream.
Gradually mix in dry gelatin.
Then fold in mandarin oranges.
Chill for several hours.

title: sticky buns
directions: The night before, grease bottom of 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put nuts in pan.
Tear bread dough into walnut-size pieces; roll into balls.
Place in pan until they just touch.
In saucepan, put brown sugar, cinnamon, milk, butter and dry pudding mix.
Heat just until butter melts.
Pour evenly over dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Immediately invert onto a plate or in another pan.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: *Works best if chicken has been skinned before using.

title: gram's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix apples, sugar and spices together with a fork.
In seperate bowl mix eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add flour and baking soda to apple mixture, then add egg mixture.
Fold in raisins.
Pour into ungreased 9x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40-50 min.
This cake is very moist.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all this and put in electric ice cream freezer for 1 hour.

title: cubed steak with gravy in crock-pot
directions: Dip steak in flour; fry until brown.
Place in crock-pot.
Add water, soup and gravy mix.
Cover and cook on low for 6 hours. Excellent served with rice.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage, onion, pepper and celery in skillet until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain well.
Bring water to boil.
Add soup mix and rice.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Combine sausage mixture and soup mixture in casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: marinated string beans
directions: Put 1 can of string beans in a dish; layer with sliced onion rings, then add other can of string beans and another layer of sliced onion.
Bring to a boil, vinegar, bean juice and sugar; after coming to a boil, add oil and Accent, then stir.
Pour over beans and onion; cover and marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours. Drain beans before serving.

title: mashed potato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening, eggs, potatoes and 4 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough of remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, then turn greased side up.
Let rise.
Punch down and cut off amount needed.
Shape and cover.
Let rise until double (about 1 1/2 hours).
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake rolls 15 to 20 minutes.
Dough can be refrigerated up to 5 days. (Punch down occasionally.)

title: party mix
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in large bowl.
Melt chocolate.
Pour over mixture; stir.
Pour mix on wax paper. Spread to dry.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: different fruit salad
directions: Mix and chill 4 hours.

title: stagecoach chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine salad dressing and egg; set aside.
Rinse chicken in icy cold water and drain well.
Dredge chicken pieces in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Dip in salad dressing-egg mixture.
Roll in cornflakes.
Arrange chicken pieces in foil-lined broiler pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Yields 4 servings.

title: stuff 'n such chicken casserole
directions: Place stuffing crumbs in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine water, butter and contents of seasoning packet in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Pour over crumb mixture; mix well.
Press some of the stuffing up along sides of casserole to create a hollow in the center.
Arrange chicken chunks in hollow area.
Blend soup and milk; pour over chicken.
May be garnished with chopped pimento and fresh parsley, if desired.
Cover and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: posole
directions: Trim off fat from pork and cut into bite-size cubes.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and seasoned salt.
Place meat, hominy (and juice from 1 can of hominy), onion, celery, carrots, chicken broth and green chilies in slow cooker.
Sprinkle with oregano and cumin; stir.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours or on high for 4 hours in a slow cooker.
When done, add cheese and milk.
Cook 15 more minutes.

title: banana split
directions: Prepare pudding with 2 cups milk according to package directions. Cover surface of pudding with waxed paper or plastic wrap. Refrigerate until cool.
Put 1 sliced banana in each of 4 serving dishes.
Top with 3 scoops of ice cream. Cover with 1/4 of the pudding.
Sprinkle with pineapple tidbits and pecans. Garnish with whipped cream and a cherry.

title: dilly bread
directions: Combine cottage cheese, sugar, minced onions, margarine, dill seed, salt, baking soda, egg, softened yeast mixutre and flour. Cover and let rise the ingredients until light and doubled in size (approximately 1 to 2 hours).
Stir down dough.
Turn into well-greased 8-inch round (1 1/2 to 2-quart) casserole.
Let rise again about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: hodge podge
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; drain.
Put cooked meat and remaining ingredients into a crock-pot.
Cook on low heat all day long.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole pan.
Add both cans of corn, sour cream and dry corn bread mix.
Blend well.
Bake in 400° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vanilla dream
directions: Heat milk, sugar and vanilla in small saucepan until mixture starts to bubble.
Pour into glass or mug.
Top with cinnamon.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spray pan with cooking spray.
Pour mixed ingredients into bread pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine all filling ingredients in a bowl, except for the water and butter.
When it is all mixed, sprinkle with the water and then put it into a baking pan (9 x 13-inch) and top with the butter.
Cover with foil; bake for 15 minutes.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: crispy crab cakes(low fat)
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spray saute pan with cooking spray and shape into small patties and saute on each side until crispy and brown.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Cool and grate.
Combine all ingredients except margarine.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour margarine over top.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pebbles cookie crispies
directions: Mix cake, oil, water, and egg in a large bowl with a wooden spoon until well blended.
Stir in cereal.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles as directed.
Drain.
Pour into casserole dish. Add 1/4 cup milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Add 5 to 6 dabs of margarine.
Cut cheese in small squares and place evenly over noodles.
Bake at 350° until cheese has melted.
Remove from oven. Let stand 10 minutes and stir to mix cheese, noodles and milk.

title: magic sour cream
directions: In an electric blender or food processor, put all ingredients. Process at high speed for 1 minute.
Pour into a heavy saucepan and cook, stirring constantly for approximately 2 minutes or until mixture has thickened and is bubbly.
Mixture foams up considerably but this recedes as it cooks.
Return to blender and process for 1 minute at high speed.
This last step is important to keep sour cream mix at a smooth consistency.
May be used as regular sour cream in cooking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in flour and cinnamon.
Add applesauce, raisins and nuts (if desired).
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cool whip cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, mandarin oranges, juice, eggs, and oil until well blended.
Pour into a greased oblong cake pan and bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool before frosting.

title: dill dip for veggies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well with fork.
Chill for at least 1 hour before serving with fresh, raw vegetables.

title: rag doll tea party
directions: For each serving, place

1 peach half for body on salad plate. Arrange 4 small celery sticks for arms and legs around peach half. Use 1 large marshmallow for head, raisins for the eyes, nose, shoes and buttons and small piece of maraschino cherry for mouth. Shred yellow cheese.
Arrange around marshmallow for hair. Add a skirt of leaf lettuce to complete salad.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar, 7-Up, jello and food coloring until thick.
Add strawberries and cook 1 minute.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Combine frozen lemonade concentrate, the strawberries that have been half-thawed with their juice and the orange juice.
Place in punch bowl with ice.

title: coconut pie
directions: Heat milk and coconut until it boils.
Mix together sugar, flour and salt.
Separate the egg yolks from the whites; beat the yolks.
Add 1/4 cup milk and beat well.
When milk boils, add the flour, sugar and salt, stirring.
Add egg yolks.
Last of all, add vanilla.
Cool until it thickens.

title: sweet potato surprise cake
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar; cream until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks one at a time.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with orange juice; beat well.
Add rind. Fold in egg whites.
Put into two 9-inch cake pans and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cornmeal, onions, eggs, corn, oil, buttermilk, peppers and salt and mix until well blended. Spoon half of mixture into greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch). Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese. Bake for 45 minutes or until done.
Cool.
Slice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german meatballs
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and form into small meatballs.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in a 375° preheated oven until brown, turning meatballs to keep them cooking through thoroughly.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Combine the meat, egg, milk, onion, celery, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix well.
Divide the mixture into 4 parts.
Mold into little loaves and place on baking dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place each chicken breast half between two sheets of waxed paper and pound lightly with a meat mallet until flattened to a 5-inch square.
Place a slice of ham and a half slice of cheese on each cutlet, cutting to fit.
Top with some of the tomato and a pinch of the sage.
Tuck in the sides and roll up, jelly roll style, pressing to seal well.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oats.
Spread into 13 x 19-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put rice, onion soup and water in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Season with salt and pepper and stir.
Place pork chops over rice mixture and cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: This is pure and simple banana bread, heavy, moist and dark.

title: jo's chicken and spaghetti
