directions: Cook chicken until very tender in enough water to cover. Remove from broth.
Add minced onion and green pepper to broth. Cook in broth for 10 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti, soups and boned chicken; heat.
(If very soupy, put in large dish and cook for 20 minutes.)
Remove from heat and add grated cheese (Velveeta cheese) to top and cook until cheese is melted in 350° oven.

title: norton's macaroni-cheese and ham casserole
directions: Boil and strain macaroni twice.
Mix cheese, milk and margarine throughly.
Add seasonings to cheese mixture.
Apply nonstick spray or margarine to a casserole dish.
Mix ham with macaroni; stir in sauce.
Gradually pour into casserole dish. Bake in oven at 275° for 35 minutes.
Serve hot to savor the flavor.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate yogurt creme dessert
directions: In medium saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and gelatin. Gradually stir in milk; let set 10 minutes.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to boil and gelatin dissolves.
Stir in yogurt and vanilla; blend until combined.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Chill until set, approximately 6 hours.
Top with Cool Whip and fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and sprinkle in onion, layer of noodles and tuna until all are used.
Mix Carnation milk and mushroom soup.
Pour over top. Top with cheese and put cracker crumbs and butter over top.
Bake at 350° until browned.

title: linguini and clam sauce
directions: Remove brown shoot from clams and chop.
Strain clam juice through cheese cloth or a stocking.
Brown garlic in pot and add clam juice and clams.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Let simmer for one hour.
Serve with linguini.

title: sunday chicken soup
directions: About 2 1/4 Hours Before Serving or Early In Day:
In 8-quart Dutch oven or saucepot over medium-high heat, in hot olive or salad oil, cook carrots, celery and onion, stirring frequently, until vegetables are golden.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Remove leaves from cabbage and immerse in hot water.
Mix cooked hamburger meat, milk and rice.
Make small balls.
Place meat in cabbage leaves and roll.
Secure with toothpicks.
Pack cabbage rolls in slow cooker or large boiler and cover with tomatoes.
Cover and simmer for about 2 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Chill several hours to allow flavors to blend.
Serve with cubed French bread or crackers.

title: bubble bread(quick garlic)
directions: Thaw softened dough.
Blend together margarine, egg, garlic powder, parsley and salt.
Cut bread dough into pieces, about walnut size.
Dip into batter mixture.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Heat together to boiling point; then simmer for 1/2 hour. Strain after cooling.
Let set (perhaps overnight).
Bring to drinking temperature before serving.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Let cool.
Punch holes in cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour cream of coconut over cake, then pour Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Spread Cool Whip evenly over entire cake and sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving and keep leftovers refrigerated.

title: sweet 'n spicy pork chops
directions: Render small amount of fat from pork chops in heavy skillet. Brown pork chops.
Remove from pan.
Add onions and cook until soft.
Return chops
to pan with remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until chops are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: brazilian honey cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
In a separate bowl, sift flour, cinnamon and baking powder together.
Mix dry ingredients into batter alternately with combined milk and honey (beginning and ending with flour mixture).
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold gently into batter.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until done. Serves 8 to 10.

title: garden salad
directions: Mix together and marinate overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add a layer of ketchup on the top 5 to 10 minutes before fully cooked.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Mix together oil, parsley, pepper, cheese and egg well in large bowl.
Cook pasta (spaghetti) and drain.
Add to bowl while hot and toss well
to coat spaghetti or mix into spaghetti while tossing.

title: fruit custard
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Stir in milk and remaining ingredients. Pour into buttered cups or a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° for about 1 hour, or until a knife inserted into center of custard comes out clean.
Serve hot with lemon sauce or very cold with hot butter sauce.

title: pumpkin muffins(weight watchers)
directions: Spray 24 muffin tins.
Fill 1/2 full.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter chocolate balls
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, stirring well.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Combine chocolate morsels and shortening in top of a double boiler (with water boiling).
Reduce heat to low, cook until the morsels melt.
Dip each peanut butter ball into the chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Makes about 9 dozen balls.

title: cherry chiffon dessert (easy & quick)
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into tart shells.
Chill well before serving.
18 servings, with a little extra filling left over.

title: beer cheese and potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes at 400° until done. Peel them and cut into chunks. Set aside. Combine beer, broth, and worcestershire sauce in a 3 qt. saucepan. Cook over med. heat for 6 min. Combine half and half and cornstarch; stir well. Add that to cheese, milk and red pepper to beer mixture; stir well. Cook and stir until thick. Add reserved potato chunks cook 2 min. Crumble bacon and cheese and chives on top.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until when pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Spread with frosting.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift
together	dry
ingredients.
Add	raisins,
nuts, melted butter and applesauce.
Beat well until blended.
Pour into greased
and
floured pan.	Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot pepper mustard
directions: Cut tops off peppers.
Grind or process, seeds and all. Process onions enough to chop.

title: wedding cake frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick paste.
Let cool in refrigerator.
After cool, mix Crisco, margarine and sugar.
Add to flour mixture with one teaspoon vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.

title: bittersweet truffles
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; stir in 3/4 cup cocoa.
Gradually add condensed milk, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth (about 3 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 8-inch square pan. Cover mixture and chill at least 2 hours and cut into squares.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix Cool Whip and Eagle Brand together.
Add chocolate milk gradually.
Pour mixture to fill line in 2-quart ice cream freezer.
Freeze as directed for electric or manual freezer.
Pour off brine.
Repack with salt and ice.
Cover with quilt or place freezer itself in grocery bag and fit another bag over from the top.
Be sure to take the dasher out before packing.

title: delicious carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients except carrots.
Mix well and cook for 20 minutes.
Add carrots.

title: white chocolate nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix cake mix (dry), margarine, brown sugar, water and egg in a large bowl, using a spoon.
Stir in walnuts and vanilla milk chips.
Press firmly in pan.
Bake 32 to 36 minutes or until top forms a crust that is dry to touch.
Cool completely.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Yield: 32 bars.

title: french fried okra
directions: Cut okra into 1-inch slices.
Sprinkle okra with salt.
Put okra in milk; stir until coated.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Drain okra well; dredge in flour.
Deep-fry okra in vegetable oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: 3 soup stew
directions: Add all ingredients to crock-pot; cook on low 6 to 8 hours. Delicious.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions (do not overcook).
Drain and soak in cold water for 10 to 15 minutes. Then drain and add mashed egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Pour vinegar over this and let set while preparing other ingredients.
Chop the egg whites.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Garnish with celery seed and paprika.
Don't use tomatoes if salad is made for next day.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
In medium bowl, mix Ricotta, spinach, 1/2 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs.
Mix well.

title: upside-down cranberry crunch
directions: Place cranberries in a greased 8-inch square baking dish. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar and pecans.

title: spring salad
directions: Cook, drain and set aside macaroni.
Put celery, onion and eggs in a bowl.
Put sugar, water, vinegar, turmeric and mayonnaise into blender until sugar dissolves.
Pour over macaroni; will be watery.
Refrigerate overnight, stirring frequently.

title: reese's cup cake
directions: Prepare the pudding according to directions. When it starts to bubble, add the dry cake mix and pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan. Crumble peanut butter cups on top and bake in a 350° oven for one half hour.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, Blue cheese, onion and garlic in bowl. Mix well with hands buttered. Shape into 1 or 2 balls. Combine Cheddar cheese, sour cream and cayenne.
Mix until smooth. Spread on surface of cheese balls. Roll into crushed nuts. Wrap with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: sunday special rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with other ingredients.
Pour into greased two-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Sunday Best Roast Beef for a real super Sunday special.

title: 10 minute chix breast and vegetables
directions: Have butcher pound chicken breasts or do it yourself with a cleaver.
Heat olive oil until medium.
Lay breasts in pan and surround them with vegetables.
Add sage, salt and pepper.
Cover pan and cook on high about 2 minutes.
Uncover.
Turn breasts over and stir vegetables.
Add wine.
Cover again for another 2 minutes. It should be done if vegetables are cut thin.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together peanut butter, sugar and egg.
If mixture is too thin for cookie dough, add a little flour (only if needed).
Form into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork to flatten and make ridges.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: wanda's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook to a boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine, then to a soft ball stage; about 2 minutes.
Add oatmeal, flavoring, peanut butter and stir.
Drop by tablespoon on wax paper.

title: chocolate chip cocoa muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except chocolate chips.
Blend until smooth.
Add chocolate chips.
Grease muffin tin and fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: aurora's tea cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, Crisco and eggs.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Roll into a loaf and then slice.
Make a frosting with powdered sugar and milk.
Spread this over the top of the cookies.
Bake at 325°.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Make lime gelatin using 1 1/4 cups hot water and 1 1/4 cups cold water.
Pour into 3 quart clear glass baking dish. Refrigerate until gelled.
Combine in saucepan, lemon gelatin, cream cheese, pineapple and marshmallows.
Cook over low heat until cream cheese melts.
Set this aside and cool slightly.

title: chocolate pecan bar
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in 1 beaten egg.
Press mixture evenly on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, beat sweetened condensed milk, remaining 1 egg and flavoring; stir in pecan halves.
Pour over prepared crust.
Spread pecan halves over top evenly.
Bake 25 minutes longer or until golden brown.
Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.

title: tamale pie(serves 6)
directions: Crumble beef into skillet.
Cook over moderate heat until meat loses red color.
Add onion, celery and garlic during about the last 5 minutes cooking time.
Drain off grease; drain tomatoes. Reserve 3/4 cup tomato sauce and mix with the cornmeal.
Cut tomatoes in small pieces.
Add cornmeal mixture.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Add corn and its liquid, olives and their liquid, chili powder, salt, Worcestershire sauce and meat mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: ski salad
directions: Stir cream cheese and milk together until consistency of salad dressing.
Peel and dice apples that have been chilled.
Add celery, raisins, nuts and apples to cheese.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: herbed fried chicken
directions: Combine biscuit mix and salad dressing mix in a plastic bag. Shake to mix.
Place 2 or 3 pieces of chicken in a bag.
Shake well.

title: fried chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine evaporated milk and egg.

In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, pepper and garlic powder. In large skillet, heat oil on medium high heat, dip chicken pieces in egg and milk mixture, then coat with flour mixture, fry in hot oil, turning frequently until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat in an electric mixer at low speed until blended.
Increase to a high speed and beat about 10 minutes.
Chill.
A wire whisk may be used instead of the mixer, beating for 30 minutes.
Serve by itself over cake or over vanilla ice cream.
Frozen strawberries are not as successful as fresh ones.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: welsh rabbit
directions: In the top of a double boiler or in a heatproof dish fitted over a pot of simmering water, heat the cheese, butter, salt, mustard and cayenne, stirring
occasionally, until the cheese melts.
Add the milk and egg, and stir constantly until the mixture thickens.
Taste and add more salt if desired.
Pour over toast.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt or tube pan, 1 hour at 350°.

title: ham balls(appetizer)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 1 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: good and easy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt shortening with syrup and water.
Add remaining ingredients. Combine and chill for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Drop teaspoons on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes.

title: pepperoni rolls
directions: Pinch dough into golf ball size balls.
Flatten by hand. Place a teaspoon sauce and 1/4-inch piece of pepperoni into each flattened dough ball.
Wrap sides around to completely cover sauce and pepperoni.
Place on greased cookie sheet smooth side up. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese while hot.

title: pork casserole
directions: Brown pork in skillet and set aside.
Spread 1/2 sauerkraut in 2-quart greased casserole.
Cover with 1 onion.
Place pork on top.
Layer onions and sauerkraut on top of pork.
Pour water over all, cover and bake at 325° for 4 hours.
Serves 6.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Heat the oil in a frying pan over a high fire.
Blend the dry ingredients.
Roll the tomatoes in dry ingredients.
Fry tomatoes in hot grease until golden brown on both sides.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Combine oats, flour, brown sugar and butter.
Crumble over apples.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Oil casserole dish.
Place ingredients in dish, starting with potatoes on the bottom and ending with soup on the top.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In blender, combine butter, oil, vermouth, garlic, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Blend on high for 10 seconds.

title: easy chocolate sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in order given.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add vanilla.
May be kept in refrigerator for beverages for flavoring and may be used as a sauce.

title: banana bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 cup of the flour, the sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas, butter or margarine and milk.
Beat until blended, then on high for 2 minutes.
Add eggs, remaining flour, vanilla, orange peel and lemon juice and blend.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: meat sauce
directions: Brown onions and meat, then add rest of the ingredients.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion in saucepan. Drain grease. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mary meskausksas' quick peanut butter fudge
directions: Mash potatoes thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter, stirring well.
Add other ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill well before cutting.

title: kedgeree
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for one hard-boiled egg, in top of double boiler.
Heat over hot water.
A teaspoon of curry powder may be added if desired for added flavor.
Serves 4.
Add sliced boiled egg over top with a little parsley.

title: baked haddock au gratin
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add flour and salt.
Stir until blended.
Slowly add milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Blend in cheese and lemon juice. Arrange haddock in a greased baking dish.
Pour cheese sauce over fish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine juice, champagne and 7-Up.
Float the sherbet.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Mix well. Batter will be thin. Pour into four 8-inch round cake pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350°. Watch carefully; will burn easily.

title: armstrong's shrimp creole
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, fry bacon, garlic, celery, onion and green pepper in olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients, except shrimp.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 hours.
Add shrimp and boil for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken pineapple salad
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons juice from pineapple with mayonnaise, mustard, curry powder and salt.
Set aside.
Cut chicken into small pieces and mix with celery, green onion, almonds and raisins.
Add mayonnaise mixture and blend well.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with lettuce and pineapple.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Layer one-half crackers, oysters and cheese.
Dot vegetable layer with butter, salt and pepper.
Place other half of crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Pour cream over all.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir salsa, corn, dressing and chili powder in a bowl.
Alternately layer all ingredients in an oblong baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: spicy mexican salsa
directions: Chop everything to desired size, food processor works well, but don't chop too fine.
Add paste to desired thickness, depending on how juicy your tomatoes are.
Add garlic, salt and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, don't overcook.
Process pints at 10 pounds pressure for ten minutes or for 30 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Makes 15 to 20 pints of salsa.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: steam baked country ham
directions: Scrub ham in warm water and soak overnight.
Place in cooking utensil with skin side up.
Add 8 to 10 cups of water.
Cover tightly and place in a cold oven.
Set temperature at 500°.
Never open door once ham has been placed in oven.
Count cooking time when oven reaches 500° and cook for 15 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave for 3 hours.
Turn oven on again and, after reaching 500°, allow to cook for another 15 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave ham in oven for 6 to 8 hours.
Skin and sprinkle with brown sugar and brown in oven.

title: chicken and chips
directions: Dip chicken in milk and egg, then mixture of crushed chips, onion powder and pepper.
Coat pan with Pam.
Put chicken in. Drizzle butter over chicken and set at room temperature for 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Dip in Ranch dressing.

title: chicken parisienne with wild rice
directions: Place chicken breasts, skin side up, in baking dish.
Combine next four ingredients.
Pour this over the chicken breasts and sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve with rice recipe.

title: mock boursin au poivre(cocktail spread)
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with garlic, caraway, basil, dill and onion.
Pat into a flat round shape on plastic wrap.
Sprinkle generously on top and bottom with lemon pepper.
Wrap completely and refrigerate.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Mix everything except flour.
Add flour gradually.
When it gets too thick, use hands to mix.
Roll about 1/2 inch thick on sugared surface.
Cut and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together butter or margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Shape 1 teaspoon of dough into small ball. Roll in mixture of 2 teaspoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Yield: 5 dozen.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll into balls and place on a cookie sheet.
Press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 32 cookies.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix and dissolve Jell-O, 4 cups water and sugar over low heat. Do not boil. Cool and add 9 cups water, pineapple juice and orange juice.

title: spiced blueberry jam
directions: Crush blueberries; measure 2 1/2 cups.
In kettle, combine berries, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to full, rolling boil.
Boil hard, uncovered, 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pectin.
Skim off foam. Pour into hot, sterilized jars.
Cover with wax or hot water seal.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips. Sprinkle with paprika and garlic powder. Cook in oil or oleo until brown. Add green pepper and onions. Cook until glazed or wilted. Add chopped tomatoes and beef broth.
Cook 20 minutes. Stir in cornstarch with soy sauce.
Cook until thick. Serve with rice.

title: lime salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into mold and chill for several hours.
This makes a large salad and will keep well if covered and refrigerated.

title: mushroom parmesan
directions: Grease shallow casserole.
Clean mushrooms with caps.
Cut off stems from caps.
Place caps, open side up in casserole.
Set aside.
Finely chop mushroom stems.
Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in skillet.
Add mushroom stems and chopped onion and garlic. Cook slowly until onion and garlic are lightly browned. Meanwhile, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and oregano.
Mix in onion, garlic and stems.
Pile mixture lightly into inverted caps.
Pour 2 tablespoons olive oil into casserole.
Cover mushrooms with Mozzarella cheese, sliced thin. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mushrooms are tender and tops are browned.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar. Add beaten egg yolk and vanilla. Mix well.
Blend in flour.
Spread evenly on cookie sheet that has all four edges
(cookies raise some). Bake in a 350° oven until starting to brown.

title: broccoli cold salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and spoon over the rest of mixture.

title: dan's beer batter
directions: Combine flour, cornstarch and salt.
Whisk in beer, butter and egg until smooth.
Can deep fry shrimp, fish, onions, etc.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and save some crumbs.
Mix all of the above, except powdered sugar.
Divide dough and make several 1-inch rolls.
Then roll each roll in wafer crumbs and powdered sugar.
Wrap each roll in wax paper and refrigerate.
Chill 24 hours and slice each roll when ready to serve.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on box. Open cream of coconut and stir well. When cake is done and while it is still hot, poke holes in the cake and spoon cream of coconut into holes. Let cake cool. When completely cool, top with Cool Whip and sprinkle generously with coconut.

title: bearcat stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cover.
Bake at 275° for 5 hours.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature.
Shred dried beef into small pieces or put through grater.
Mix all ingredients, leaving enough dried beef out to roll in after you form ball. Chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients;
add shortening.
Store in refrigerator
several hours before use.
May be used in muffin pan or rolled out and cut.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: layer bean dip
directions: Put beans into large casserole dish.
Mix olives, green chilies and sour cream together (or layer).
Put on top of beans. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter, and mix well; then add butter. Bake until brown at 400°.

title: peppers with cream cheese filling
directions: Rinse and dry peppers.
With a sharp knife, cut off the stem end, leaving a small round of pepper attached.
Discard stem and finely chop the remaining part.
Remove the seeds carefully, without breaking the skins.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off excess oil.
Mix altogether with remaining ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: grilled cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and dry ingredients.
Add 2/3 cheese (grated) and pepperoni.
Bake 25 minutes in pie plate.
Take out and put rest of cheese on top and bake 2 more minutes at 425°.

title: tobacco stick driving casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with sausage seasoning and celery in a large skillet, stirring until meat crumbles.
Drain and pat dry.
Add next 4 ingredients to hamburger.
Stir.

Put a layer of Velveeta on top of hamburger mixture then place top on skillet to allow cheese to melt or spoon hamburger mixture into a 2-quart casserole, then layer Velveeta on top and microwave for five minutes on Medium.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Flour and brown chicken in 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spoon in 2 or 3 spoonfuls of spaghetti sauce to cover bottom of pan.
Place chicken in pan and cover with remaining sauce.
Place a slice of cheese on each chicken breast. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Make sure chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: potato pone
directions: Wash potatoes.
Remove spots.
Do not peel.
Grate potatoes. Add all other ingredients.
Heat oil and butter;
add potato mixture. Make sure it does not stick.
The pone will be finished when it turns almost brown in color.
Transfer to two 9 inch pie pans.
Let cool.
Slice.

title: jalapeno peppers
directions: Wash peppers and cut in half.
Remove seeds.
Pat dry; fill with cream cheese.
Wrap bacon around peppers.
Bake in a 350° oven about 25 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: e z lasagna
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in sauce.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread a little sauce.
Layer uncooked noodles, top with 1/2 the cottage cheese, then layer of sauce and then 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Repeat.
Blend together eggs and milk and pour over lasagna.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered, or until egg mixture is solid.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: tuna-macaroni-cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain and rinse.
Stir celery into macaroni.
Place 1/2 of macaroni mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Flake tuna in a large bowl.
Combine salt, pepper and cheese with tuna.
Sprinkle macaroni mixture with 1/2 the tuna mixture.
Repeat layers (first macaroni, then tuna).
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in saucepan over low heat; stir in flour and remaining salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream and broth.
Return to heat, stirring constantly, until sauce boils.
Pour sauce over tuna mixture and dot with 1 tablespoon of butter.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Bake another 15 minutes or until sauce turns golden brown.

title: sour jack rice
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
In greased casserole dish layer rice mixture alternately with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Recipe doubles easily.

title: lentil and tomato bake
directions: Grate carrots and chop tomatoes; set aside.
Wash lentils, removing any small stones.
In large saucepan, combine with 2 cups of water.
Wrap bay leaf around onion and push cloves through leaf into onion.
Add to pan with carrots and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Lower heat and cover; simmer about 20 minutes. Remove onion; add salt, margarine and parsley.
Stir well.
Spoon into large ovenproof dish.
Dot top with margarine and bake in 375° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Combine sour cream, lemon juice and seasonings in shallow dish.
Place breasts in sour cream mixture, turning to coat. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups unbleached white flour, 1/2 cup oats, salt and yeast.
Mix well.
Add honey and hot water.
Beat 200 strokes, 1 to 2 minutes.
Use all of the whole wheat flour, mixing thoroughly. Let dough rise 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup white flour on dough, coating all sides, scraping the bowl side, so flour will coat dough.
Put on table, knead 10 to 15 minutes, until dough bounces back.
Shape in rolls or a loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Process and store same as Cappuccino.

title: nachos
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off oil.
Add taco seasoning mix and 1 cup water.
Stir in chili, refried beans, picante sauce and 1 cup water.
Let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Arrange tortilla chips on baking sheet and pour mixture over tortilla chips. Sprinkle grated cheese over top and bake at 350° until cheese starts to bubble.
You may garnish with lettuce, tomatoes, onions and jalapeno peppers.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil 5 minutes, brown sugar, corn syrup and butter.
Add soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Pour over corn in large bowl or cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir often.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: Add milk to peanut butter, a small amount at a time, blending until smooth. Stir in corn syrup. Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: scalloped corn and oyster casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle over top a mixture of 1/2 cup cracker crumbs and 2 tablespoons oleo. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cereal mix party scramble
directions: Mix all ingredients, coating all cereal.
Bake in low oven for 30 minutes, more or less.

title: marinated bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Make into medium size balls and roll them in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: paprika potatoes
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan and saute the onion and green pepper for about 3 minutes.
Add the potatoes and saute for about five minutes.
Add paprika and stir to coat the potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients and just enough water to barely cover. Reduce heat and cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender and water is almost absorbed.
Drain before serving if potatoes are tender and too much liquid remains.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add California Blend vegetables.
Boil 10 minutes more.
Add cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese melts.
Very good.

title: spinach balls
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze
out all extra water.	Combine with other ingredients.	Roll into
inch
balls and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tin roof pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well and press firmly on bottom and sides of a buttered 9-inch
pie
plate.
Spread ice cream over crust.
Cover and freeze
overnight
or
until firm to serve.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup and sprinkle with peanuts. Makes 1 pie.

title: fruit-nut nibbles
directions: Mix cereal, peanuts and bananas in 3-quart bowl.
Mix margarine, honey, cinnamon and salt; pour over cereal mixture, tossing until evenly coated.
Microwave under cover on High (100%) for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave until toasted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Watch carefully so that mixture does not burn.
(May use regular oven to toast.) Stir in popcorn, coconut and raisins.
Let cool for 1 hour.
Store in tightly covered container 1 week.

title: mott's fabulous fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of pan.
Mix ingredients into large bowl.
Beat 50 strokes.
Bake 33 to 35 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: refreshing diet fruit punch
directions: Mix all items in a large punch bowl. Serve over ice cubes or add ice to punch.

title: upside-down pizza loaf(weight watchers)
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet heat 1/2 teaspoon oil; add turkey and onion and, using back of a wooden spoon to crumble meat, cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is tender and turkey is no longer pink.

Sprinkle mixture with 1 tablespoon flour and stir quickly to combine; cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Gradually stir in tomato sauce; add bell pepper, basil, fennel seed and oregano and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring frequently, for 1 minute.

title: cabbage italiano
directions: Cut cabbage into 1-inch square pieces and put in a 5-quart Dutch oven.
Add water and start to cook on low heat.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces and add to cabbage.
Add tomatoes and juice; stir well.
Cover and cook until sausage is done.
Cooking time: approximately 30 minutes.

title: pecan cheese ball
directions: Reserve 1 cup pecans.
Mix remaining ingredients and roll into ball.
Roll cheese ball in reserved nuts.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: ground black pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch strips.
Cover with pepper to taste. Brown in oil.
Add minced onions and broth.
Cover; cook 1 hour. Remove steak from pan.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in small saucepan.
Add 3 tablespoons flour to make a paste.
Add to broth; turn up heat.
Stir constantly until thick.
This can be done in crock-pot.

title: mcgee's lasagna
directions: Brown ground chuck and add onion (drain if needed).
Boil noodles.
In a long casserole dish (butter the bottom), place 1 layer noodles, 1 layer meat, 1 layer cheese (cottage) and 1 layer other cheese.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: milwaukee potato soup
directions: Boil the potatoes and onion in salted water until soft.
Drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter in same pan. Stir in flour and brown slightly. Combine milk and 1 cup reserved liquid. Stir into flour mixture. Stir and cook until thickened. Add the potatoes, mashed slightly.
Serve with cheese sprinkled on top.

title: desperation stew
directions: Boil potatoes and onion with just enough water to cover.
When tender, add peas (do not drain) and corned beef chopped into chunks; heat through.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into prepared pie shell.
Cover edge with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until done.
After cool, top with whipped cream.

title: veggie bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls in bottom of greased jelly roll pan. Also, push rolls up the sides.
Smooth seams well.
Bake in 350° oven 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine soup, eggs, cheese, onion and mayonnaise, then pour over broccoli. Sprinkle stuffing mix over the top, then dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and oil together.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and put in 3 (1 pound) bread pans, greased.
Fill half full and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cover bottom of pastry shell with ham. Set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine cream, milk, eggs, grated cheese, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Pour mixture over ham. Arrange asparagus tips on top, as if spokes of a wheel, tips in the center.
Bake in center of oven 35 to 40 minutes or until set and golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mandarin chocolate pie
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups milk into medium bowl. Add pudding mix and whisk until blended. While still thin, pour into pie crust. Spread evenly. This will thicken quickly.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Refrigerate 5 minutes.
Combine whipped topping and condensed milk; stir into chilled pudding.
Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with cookies, banana slices and filling; repeat, ending with crushed cookies. Makes 16 servings.

title: lazy lasagna(serves 8; quick and easy)
directions: Pre-cook noodles for 5 minutes.
Drain noodles.
Heat oven to 375°.
While noodles are cooking, mix 3 cheeses in a bowl (large). Fold in warm noodles.
Warm spaghetti sauce and add ground beef or turkey (if desired).
Cover bottom of pan with sauce.
Add half noodle mixture.
Then add sauce.
Add other half noodles and rest of sauce.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: rainy clouds
directions: Will also need 12 small cups.

title: hot dog creole
directions: Cut frankfurters into 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook and stir frankfurters in large skillet over medium heat until brown.
Stir in corn (with liquid), tomato sauce, chili powder, salt and onion. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes. Cook macaroni as directed on package; add frankfurter sauce over macaroni and sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: snack crackers
directions: Add oil to crackers; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Store in airtight containers.

title: amazing cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Pour into pan; spoon fruit over top.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: super salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp and break into pieces. Cut cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces. Put in large bowl. Chop onions and green pepper and add to vegetables. Add bacon, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: kicklach
directions: Beat eggs until light, then beat in oil, sugar, flour and salt. Beat until very smooth.
Stir in poppy seeds, if you desire.

title: jello surprise
directions: Heat water (boiling) and dissolve Jell-O and add 1 cup cold water which includes juice drained from pineapple.
Chill until almost firm.
Add pineapple and pie filling (sometimes I use cherry filling).
Stir to mix well.
Chill.

title: tropical sour cream dessert
directions: Blend flour, oleo and pecans.
Press into bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°; cool.
Combine pineapple, sugar, milk and pudding mix in a medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add a small amount of hot mixture to sour cream, mixing well.
Add sour cream mixture to remaining hot mixture, mixing well.
Stir in coconut; allow to cool.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Separate eggs.
Set aside whites and allow to return to room temperature.
Beat egg yolks with shortening and butter at high speed until well blended.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add extracts and beat. At low speed, beat in flour, about 1/4 at a time, alternating with milk, about 1/3 at a time.
Begin and end with flour.
Add coconut and beat.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold whites into batter.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake for 2 hours or until cake tester inserted comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix thoroughly the ingredients and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: italian pie
directions: Mix eggs with Ricotta cheese.
Add Parmesan cheese, salt, parsley, garlic and pepper.
Mix well.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed until fluffy and gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating mixture after each addition.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 18 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool completely on racks.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and rinse spaghetti.
Dice vegetables into small cubes. Blend in dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add vegetable cubes and toss.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: mushrooms on toast
directions: Saute 1
onion
and
mushrooms in butter for a few minutes. Add
flour,
parsley,
bay
leaf,
nutmeg, bouillon and tomatoes; cook until onion and mushrooms are tender (about 15 minutes).
Add sherry
and
serve garnished with parsley over toast.

title: "chicken lickin' good" pork chops
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Coat chops lightly with mixture.
Brown in oil in large skillet.
Place browned chops in crock-pot.
Add soup.
Cover and cook on low (250°) 6 to 8 hours.

title: hot deviled ham sandwich
directions: Spread bread with salad dressing.
Then make 6 sandwiches, adding a slice of cheese to each.
Mix ham and relish together and add to sandwiches.
Add tomato slices next, and top with reserved slices of cheese.
Cover with remaining bread.
Brush with melted margarine and grill on both sides until lightly browned.

title: gazpacho(cold vegetable soup)
directions: Crush the garlic and chopped pepper in a mortar with a little salt.
Add the tomatoes, which have been cut into pieces and the moistened bread crumbs.
When everything has been well crushed, add olive oil little by little, stirring continuously.
When it has been absorbed, add cold water and then strain it off.
Add vinegar and salt and serve very cold with croutons as accompaniment.

title: spicy oven pork chops
directions: In large open roasting pan, mix soy sauce, sherry and water. Place pork chops in soy sauce mixture, turning each chop to coat well.
Bake in 375° oven 40 minutes.
With pastry brush, baste chops occasionally with soy sauce mixture in pan.
Meanwhile, in 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in catsup and remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Brush chops with half of catsup mixture; cook 10 minutes.
Turn chops; brush with remaining catsup mixture.
Bake 20 minutes longer or until chops are fork-tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch dish in order listed.
Serve with big Fritos.

title: stuffed deviled crabs
directions: To white sauce, add beaten egg, catsup, salt, green pepper and Mexene; mix with crabmeat.
Pack mixture into crab shells; sprinkle with cracker meal.
Garnish with Mexene seasoning and bake until crumbs are brown.

title: freezer ice cream
directions: Beat all ingredients in an ice cream freezer.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: You will need 1 crock-pot, measuring cups and spoons and 1 large spoon.

title: sweet-sour sauce
directions: In 1-quart saucepan with spoon, stir sugar, cornstarch and chili powder until well mixed; stir in water, catsup and cider vinegar until smooth.
Over medium-high heat, cook until mixture is thickened and boils, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in chopped sweet pickle or pickle relish.

title: variety cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and add sugars; beat well.
Add eggs and continue beating.
Add dry ingredients, vanilla and 1 or more of the suggested ingredients.
If coconut is added, coconut flavoring adds something extra to the taste.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.
Place pieces of dough about the size of a walnut on a cookie sheet and bake at 325°.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl and make a well in center.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Stir just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly and remove from tins.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream together sugars, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Blend these two mixtures together and mix well.
Then add apples.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove from pan in about 15 minutes.
Can be frozen.
A very moist cake!!

title: shannon's chicken and mushrooms
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter until slightly browned.
Add cut-up chicken and saute until white (about 3 minutes).
Add garlic salt and soup.
Stir in 1/2 can of water.
Simmer about 2 minutes. Serve over rice, mashed potatoes or baked potato.

title: christmas applesauce and cinnamon ornaments
directions: Blend applesauce and spices.
Knead.
Roll on wax paper to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Let dry on wax paper for 4 to 5 days (will shrink).
Use straw to cut hole in top.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Stir together flour and sugar.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir up.
Add pecans; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake in ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes until light brown. Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
I use red wine vinegar and NutraSweet instead of sugar.
This salad keeps well at least a week.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter; add corn syrup, sugar and chocolate chips.
After all ingredients are melted, add eggs, flour and nuts.
Place in 9-inch round cake pan that has been buttered and lightly floured. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes, then put on glaze and chill.

title: chicken albergetti
directions: Cook noodles according to directions. Set aside.
Pound chicken breasts flat.
Dip breasts in water, shake off, then place in bread crumbs to coat.
Brown both sides in frying pan with oil. Remove and set aside. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, chicken and spaghetti sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Delicious!

title: sausage cheese puffs
directions: Fry sausage, drain grease and let cool.
Grate Cheddar cheese and mix with cooled sausage.
Add Bisquick mix, using water as needed to make thick consistency to form into balls.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Measure sugar and cornstarch into saucepan; mix well.
Add pineapple and juice.
Mix well so no lumps form.
Stir in pie filling and food color.
Use wood spoon.
Stir gently to avoid mashing.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil and is well thickened (about 5 to 8 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in dry jello.
Let cool completely, then gently stir in banana slices.
Spoon mix into baked pie shells.
Cover top with whipped topping and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: biscuit bread
directions: Cut butter into self-rising flour with a pastry blender until crumbly; add milk and water, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead 3 or 4 times. Pat dough into a 7-inch circle on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Cut a 1/2-inch deep X in top of dough; spray dough with cooking spray. Bake at 425° for 25-30 minutes or until lightly browned and done.

title: lemon pepper chicken with fettucine
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium-high heat, bring first 7 ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Boil gently uncovered for 10 minutes.
Add cream.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover. In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook mushrooms and garlic in melted butter until browned and any liquid has evaporated.
Add to cream sauce.
Place chicken on broiler pan. Sprinkle both sides with lemon juice and cracked pepper.
Broil 4 inches from heat source, 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until no longer pink in center.

title: mom's pineapple pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat egg yolks and milk together; add to flour.
Cook in a heavy saucepan until thick.
Add pineapple and salt.
Pour into 9-inch baked shell and top with meringue.
Makes 2 pies.
Serves 16.

title: peanut butter munchies
directions: Melt chips, peanut butter and butter.
Pour cereal in very large bowl.
Cool.
Coat with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate mint patties
directions: Sift together sugar and cocoa; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, corn syrup and peppermint extract at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually add 1 to 2 cups of cocoa and sugar mixture, beating with a wooden spoon until well blended; stir in the remaining cocoa mixture.
With hands, knead mixture until it is well blended and smooth.
On wax paper, pat or roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
With small cookie cutters or cutters of your choice, cut into desired shapes. Refrigerate in tightly covered container.
You can garnish these if so desired.
Makes about
7 dozen.

title: ginger-beef stir-fry
directions: Thaw pea pods.
Partially freeze beef.
Thinly slice across the grain into bite-size strips.
For sauce, combine sherry, soy sauce, cornstarch, ground ginger (if using) and 1/3 cup water. Set aside.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Let cake cool and frost.

title: coconut-pineapple carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 18-inch baking pan for 40 minutes.
Top cake with any favorite brand of cream cheese frosting.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Cut biscuits into quarters and roll in sugar/cinnamon mix.
Make sauce by heating brown sugar and butter or margarine in pan until sugar is melted.
Stir well. Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Layer coated biscuit sections into pan, covering each layer with some sauce and chopped pecans.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: aunt arpie's sauerkraut
directions: Pour boiling water over and seal.
Store in a cool, dark place.
Set
jars
on
newspaper because they might work loose. They will seal themselves back.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Grease 9-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat together butter, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour mixture and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Simmer broccoli, onions and potatoes in broth for 20 minutes or until tender. Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil. Serve hot.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and cream cheese together.
Then add flour and eggs alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
This is wonderful too, if you add coconut!
Don't use a mixer on this!

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add the next 6 ingredients; simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package; drain.
Mix the cream cheese and sour cream.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kevin's peach pie-cream peach pie
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 10-inch deep dish pie pan.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed the flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, oleo and milk.
Pour into pie pan.
Drain the peaches and set aside.
Place peaches on top of the mixture in pie pan.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons peach syrup. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon over peaches, forming it up into about 1/2-inch from edge of pan.
Mix together the cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Sprinkle on top. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
This is wonderful.

title: veal goulash
directions: Place 1 to 2 cups flour with salt and pepper in a bag.
Cube veal and add to flour mixture.
Shake to coat meat, then brown in lightly greased pan.
Add remainder of ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: seven layers of goodness
directions: Take a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Make graham cracker crust out of butter and crumbs.
Pat firmly in bottom of pan.
Then spread layer of chocolate chips, layer of butterscotch chips and a layer of coconut.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over this (optional), then condensed milk spread over entire top.

title: emergency casserole
directions: Arrange potatoes in bottom of 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with thinly sliced onion and top with milk and butter.
Spread corn evenly on top.
Arrange sliced corned beef over corn.
Crumble soft bread crumbs over meat.
Spam may be used instead of corned beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes longer or until hot and bubbly.

title: french onion soup
directions: In crock-pot, add ingredients.
Bring to boil; turn down to low and let simmer 2 or 3 hours.
Serve with croutons or French bread.
Makes 10 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash into bite-size pieces; boil for 10 minutes and drain.
Melt butter with squash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: wild rice with caramelized onions
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onions and brown sugar.
Cook about 6 minutes until onions are soft and translucent.
Reduce heat to low.
Slowly cook onions, stirring often, about 25 minutes or until they are caramel color.
Stir in the cranberries.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes until cranberries swell.

title: spicy hot chocolate
directions: Spoon mix into cup; add hot milk and rum.
Stir until well blended. Garnish with whipped cream and cinnamon.

title: banana nut coffee cake with caramel icing
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Grease either a Bundt or tube pan and set aside.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice separately.
Saute celery and onion in margarine; drain.
Mix all together and cook 15 minutes at 450°.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Boil and drain macaroni.
Grate cheese into 2 1/2-quart dish. Pour warm macaroni over cheese.
Stir.
Add 1 can of evaporated milk and slightly beaten egg.
Finish filling dish with whole milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter. Add vanilla and sugar. Form into balls the size of marbles. Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler. Dip balls in chocolate. Place on wax paper to cool.

title: white potato pie
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in boiling water with a little salt. Mash potatoes fine.
Add other ingredients and enough milk to make batter.
Makes 3 thick pies.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until a little browning on top appears or clean knife inserted in center of pies comes out clean.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Cook to soft ball.
Pour over popped corn.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix box and add sour cream to prepared mix.
Bake in greased Bundt pan at 350°.
Serve plain or with your favorite glaze.

title: hamburger spanish rice
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef, onion, green pepper and rice. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma lowe's cole slaw
directions: Wash and shred cabbage and carrots.
Add mayonnaise, milk, sugar to taste, pickles, raisins and carrots.
Mix and serve.

title: bran muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder; set aside. In large mixing bowl, combine Kellogg's All-Bran with extra fiber cereal and milk.
Let stand 5 minutes or until cereal softens.
Add egg and oil; mix well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into 12 lightly greased 2 1/2-inch muffin-pan cups.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and rinse in colander.
Cool.
Add diced boiled eggs (small pieces).
Add diced onion, pickles, celery and tomatoes (all chopped and diced).
Add the jar of pimentos.
Add diced olives, salt and pepper.
Add dressing; mix well.
Sprinkle paprika.
It can be done ahead, even the day before!

title: one dish chicken and potatoes
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Put chicken in pan; add peeled potatoes, cut in medium size chunks.
Add mushrooms, cover with soy sauce, then completely cover with soups (depending on how much sauce you want).
Cover with foil; bake at 375° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
To brown, remove foil for last half hour.

title: rita's famous holiday pickles
directions: Drain pickles and replace back in jar.	Add sugar, onion, celery seed, horseradish and vinegar.
Mix and store in refrigerator for 3 weeks in large jar, turning every 24 hours. Place in small jars and seal or cap.
Keep refrigerated.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Cut bacon fine and fry.
Brown onion in fat and add vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Allow to boil, then add potatoes and parsley.
Heat thoroughly and serve.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Empty one can of beans into bottom of greased casserole. Combine onion, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce; sprinkle over beans.
Top with second can of beans.
Spread catsup over beans; top with bacon pieces.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or until bacon is done.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: steak in sauce
directions: Cut steak into serving pieces and place in baking pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and bake in oven at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
If desired, may add potatoes at same time; slice potatoes in half.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Cook rice 5 minutes and mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shish kabob marinade
directions: Marinate meat, cut in cubes for skewers, and fresh mushrooms several hours, turning occasionally.
Suggestions for Shish Kabobs:
canned pearl onions, canned new potatoes, pineapple chunks, bell pepper and cherry tomatoes.
Put meat on skewer first, then desired ingredients alternately.
Cook on grill until meat is done.

title: oven herb chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing mix, soft butter and paprika.
Roll chicken in mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in greased pan for 1 hour at 375°.

title: yellow squash finger style
directions: Cut unpeeled squash into finger style.
Stir together the eggs, water, corn mix, salt, and pepper to taste.
Dip fingers into mix, gently hit on the side of bowl so fingers won't be over covered. Deep fry in your favorite oil until golden brown.
Drain well on a brown paper bag.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: Saut onion, pepper, garlic and chicken in oil several minutes.
Add tomatoes and saute a few more minutes. Add chicken broth and tomato soup, cumin, chili powder, lemon pepper and Worcestershire sauce. Simmer 1 1/2 hours. Garnish with tortilla strips and cheese.

title: blender custard pie
directions: Pour all ingredients into a blender.
Mix for 1 minute.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Using
a
quart casserole dish, brown ground beef in microwave or on stove top.
Drain off grease.
Stir in Spanish rice and refried beans.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30
minutes
or
minutes
in the microwave.
Serve with Doritos.

title: old fashioned texas pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake in oven on 325 to 350 degrees.
Bake approximately 50 minutes to and hour.

title: one bowl buttercream frosting
directions: In small bowl, cream butter.
Add cocoa and sugar alternately with milk; beat to spreading consistency (more milk may be needed).
Blend in vanilla.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss lettuce, ground beef, cheese, tomato and Doritos in large bowl. Mix mayonnaise and taco sauce together. Pour over salad and toss.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt. Add milk gradually. While cooking add butter and vanilla. Cook till thick. Pour into greased or wax paper lined dish, cool, and cut into squares.

title: 15 bean soup
directions: Put washed beans in pan; add 2 tablespoons salt.
Cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain; add 2 quarts water and ham hocks.
Boil, then simmer, for 2 hours.
Add potato and carrot; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add lemon juice, tomatoes and onion; simmer 1/2 hour more.
Season to taste.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Butter 9x13 casserole dish.
Line bottom with bread cubes. Mix all other ingredients together and pour over bread cubes. Cover and refrigerate over night.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir gently to blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: lo-cal grape spread
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Bring grape juice to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add softened gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add sweetener and bring to a full boil.
Fill jars and seal.
Can refrigerate.

title: brunch enchiladas
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs with water.
Add enough hot sauce so the eggs are bright orange.
In another bowl, combine the flour and pepper.
Season the chicken with the House Seasoning.
Dip the chicken in the egg mixture and then coat well in the flour mixture.

title: sand bakkels
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar; add egg and almond.
Add flour to make stiff dough.
Pinch off small balls and press into center of small cookie tins; shape up sides.
Place tins on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool before removing from tins. May be served as is or fill with
favorite filling.

title: colombian holiday bread(mantecada)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix butter, sugar and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
In another bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, salt, cornstarch and baking powder.
Add dry ingredients and eggs to butter mixture, alternating 1/2 cup flour, then 2 eggs, etc., mixing well with each addition until smooth and creamy.
Mix in lemon juice (or rum) and raisins.
Grease 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) and 2 (8 x 8-inch) square pans.
Pour batter into pans about 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes, until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to 1 cup hot water.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix altogether.
Pour into baking dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350°.
Stick knife in middle; it if comes out clean or if it cracks in the middle, it's all done.

title: old-fashion carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 300° until brown.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put coconut in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Mix cake according to directions.
Spread on top of nuts.
Mix oleo (melted), cream cheese and powdered sugar well; dab on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: party meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Mix with meat, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Roll into bite size balls.
Place into dish.

title: chicken salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple well.
Mix all ingredients with cole slaw dressing or mayonnaise.
Chill and serve.

title: sugarless fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in juice from fruit, heated.
Mix together first four ingredients.
Sprinkle pudding over mixture.
Add dissolved gelatin.
Mix well and cover.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: mexican cookies
directions: Blend butter and flour. Add grated cheese and seasonings, then Rice Krispies. With hands, press into small circles.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: hanky pankys
directions: Cube Velveeta into small pieces.
Fry beef and sausage.
Drain well and reheat.
Mix cheese cubes and spices with heated meats. Mix well until meat, cheese and spices are well-blended.

title: yam puff
directions: Cook yams or sweet potatoes.
Cover and boil in just enough salted water to cover until they can be pierced easily with a fork, about 40 minutes.
Cool and peel.

title: mock cherry pie
directions: Take cold water in a saucepan and allow to boil for 5 minutes. Thicken with starch or flour; allow to cool.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: pineapple crescents
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Reserve 2 spears for sauce. Chop
and set aside.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Wrap ham and cheese around pineapple.
Place at widest part of crescent and roll
up. Place
on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Fold together jello, water and cranberries.
Put in refrigerator until slightly firm.
Fold in sour cream and chopped nuts; pour into mold.

title: fruit medley
directions: In a bowl, combine the pie filling, pineapple, oranges, cherries and bananas.
Cover and refrigerate.
Just before serving stir in pecans.
Serves 8-10.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Lay chicken, skin side down, in shallow open pan.
Add sliced onion and garlic.
Pour in water to fill pan about 3/4-inch.
Cook in a 375° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water; set aside.
Cream together oleo, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs to above.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichoke hearts.
Mix with other ingredients.
Turn into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly and slightly browned.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake layers.
Split in half.
Put pineapple, cherry and banana pie filling between each layer.
Top with pecans until you fill punch bowl up.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Pour boiling water on dates (let sit).
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and cocoa in large mixing bowl.
Combine in a separate bowl the oil, egg, vanilla and dates with water; mix. Add wet ingredients to dry ones and mix well.
Pour into 10 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in ice cream churn and freeze. Tastes like Wendy's Frosty!

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Mix well and pour in large pie pan greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Beat egg well.
Add sugar and vinegar; mix well.
Let come to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Cool. Pour over salted, chopped cabbage, tossing gently.

title: fried rice with meat
directions: Cook rice until done.
Separate until fluffy and dry.
This rice should not be watery.
Let the rice set.
Cut the carrots and onions in thin slices.
Dice the peppers.

title: cream wafer cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, cream and flour.
Cover and chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll about 1/3 of dough at a time (1/8 inch thick) on floured cloth-covered board.
(Keep remaining dough refrigerated until ready to roll.)
Cut into 1 1/2 inch circles, very small circles.
Transfer rounds with spatula to piece of waxed paper that is covered with sugar; coat both sides with sugar.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick rounds with fork about 4 times. Bake 7 to 9 minutes or just until set but not brown; cool.
Put cookies in pairs with Creamy Filling.

title: jalapeno corn
directions: Cook corn as directed and drain.
Drop in cheese and stir until melted.
Add peppers to taste.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together in large bowl.
Transfer to 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
While that's baking, melt margarine and mix with corn flakes.
Put this mixture on potato mixture and bake 20 minutes more for a total of 1 hour.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt cheese and butter on low heat together. Add cocoa and powdered sugar. Mix together. Add vanilla and pecans.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Pare and cube eggplant.
Cook until tender and drain well. Saute onion and celery in butter until soft.
Drain tomatoes and chop with eggplant.
Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until brown.

title: fish chowder
directions: In heavy 3-quart saucepan, saute onion, celery, Worcestershire sauce, butter and celery salt over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
Place fish on top of sauteed vegetables.
Cover; lower heat and cook 10 minutes.
(Fish can be frozen.)
With fork, break up fish into pieces.
Add soup, milk, salt and white pepper to taste.
Add parsley and chives if desired.
Simmer slowly for 15 minutes.
Add shrimp or crab and heat until warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together.
Just before serving, add crushed chips and dressing.
Toss and serve.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl pour boiling water over oats.
Let it stand for 10 minutes.
Stir in sugar, brown sugar and soft margarine.
Add eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa; add.
Stir in half of the chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread remaining chips and walnuts or pecans, coarsely chopped on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Take crescent rolls and press into a 9-inch pie plate to make a crust.
In a skillet, brown ground beef; saute onions and drain.
Stir in mushrooms and Ragu sauce.

title: english toffee dessert(doubled recipe works great! freezes indefinitely.)
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar together, add beaten egg yolks, melted chocolate, and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into any size casserole dish and top with vanilla wafer crumbs. Serves 8.

title: 24 hour christmas salad
directions: Combine eggs,
sugar,
lemon juice and 1/4 cup whipping cream. Cook in
double boiler until thick, like dressing.	Mix with fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: You will need a blender, grater, large bowl, stirring spoon, wax paper for tabletop and storage container.

title: maple walnut bubble bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine 2 cups flour, brown sugar, yeast and salt. In a small sauce pan, heat water, milk and 5 tablespoons butter until very warm; combine with dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs and enough remaining flour to make soft dough.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine the
sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine in a pot. Bring to a
boil,
then
let boil for about a minute, stirring carefully.	Remove	from
the heat and add the vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix
well, then drop by spoonful onto wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: chocolate turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels, milk and margarine together while cake is baking.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: do ahead freezer meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into 2 dozen meatballs.
Place in a shallow baking pan.
Bake at 370° for 25 minutes.
Package and freeze for future use.

title: cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into a ball. Tear off individual strips and roll into a straw.
Place straws on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, buttermilk and grated cheese together.
Melt butter or margarine in saucepan.
Add parsley and garlic powder. Coat drop biscuits with butter mix.
Place on cookie sheet and spoon on the remaining butter mixture.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 10 to 12 large biscuits.

title: seashell casserole
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and saute with chopped celery and onion until bacon browns slightly.
(Drain grease from bacon.) Add tomatoes (chopped) and simmer while pasta is boiling.
Place half of seashells, sauce and chopped cheese in buttered casserole, then put second half in ending with the cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until edges are slightly brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine
sugar,
flour, eggs and milk in boiler and boil until thick.
Add vanilla, lemon juice and beaten eggs.
Return to heat and
cook
about
minute.
Remove from heat and add butter. Pour into pan with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Chill.

title: quick caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Stir in brown sugar and cook on low for 2 minutes. Add milk and bring to a full boil. Cool to lukewarm. Add confectioners sugar. Beat until smooth and spread on cool cake.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Melt margarine in an 11 x 8-inch pan.
Drain broccoli well. Mix all ingredients together well and pour into the well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole 4
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving enough dry dressing to put on top of casserole.
Place in a greased casserole.
Dot margarine over squash mixture.
Cover with reserved dry dressing.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: tangy onions
directions: Peel onions and cut a small slice from the top, leaving the root end whole.
Cut each onion from the top into 8 wedges, taking care not to cut through the root end.
Brush 4 sheets of aluminum foil with olive oil.
In a small bowl, mix vinegar, oregano, brown sugar, salt and pepper and rub this mixture on all surfaces of the onions.
Wrap each onion in a sheet of aluminum foil.
Bake at 350 degrees for an hour or until tender.
In the last 5 minutes of baking, open the foil and sprinkle with the bread crumbs.

title: guacamole(serves 4)
directions: Peel the avocado and discard the pit.
Cut the avocado into cubes (approximately 3 cups).
Put the avocado in a mixing bowl and cut it back and forth with a knife to make a coarse-fine mixture.
Add the grated onion, garlic, minced chilies, chopped onion, lime juice, crushed coriander seed, tomato, olive oil and radish.
Add the coriander.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Sift flour and add sugar, baking powder and salt.
Put buttermilk in large bowl and add cooking oil.
Add to yeast and work in flour.
Knead well on floured board.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.
You may use as much or as little as you wish at a time.

title: grandma phillips' jelly roll
directions: Mix ingredients quickly.
Spread thinly on a greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until just golden brown around the edges.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Add cornmeal and mix thoroughly.
Combine egg, milk and shortening. Pour into flour mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Do not beat.
Turn onto greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake in a 400° to 425° oven for approximately 25 minutes.

title: tortoni squares(serves 12)
directions: Mix nuts, oleo, wafers and extract.
Put 1/3 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan or dish.
Top with 1/2 of the ice cream (softened to spreading consistency).
Put in freezer until firm.
Top with 1/2 of the preserves.
Repeat with 1/3 of the crumb mixture, remainder of the ice cream.
Return to freezer until firm.
Add remainder of the preserves and top with remainder of crumb mixture.
Freeze. Delicious for summer dessert!

title: chicken pie
directions: In greased shallow casserole dish, arrange in layers:
1 1/2 c, stuffing mix, then cubed chicken.
Combine two cans of cream of chicken soup with one cup of hot chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Moisten 2 2/3 c. stuffing mix with 4 tbsp. melted butter and 3/4 c. hot chicken broth.
Spread over casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet sauerkraut
directions: Mix sauerkraut, crushed tomatoes and sugar.
Place in pan. Arrange bacon on top.
Bake uncovered in 300° oven for 2 hours. Cut up bacon; mix in and bake one more hour for a total of 3 hours.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix in sugar, vanilla and vinegar.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: dill pickles
directions: Fill a 2-quart jar with cucumbers and dill.
Add alum.
Bring vinegar, salt and water to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Seal while hot.

title: rugelach
directions: Blend the first three ingredients with a fork or wire pastry blender.
Add the flour gradually and blend thoroughly.
Gather into a ball and knead about 10 times.
Divide into 6 pieces; wrap each in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix sugar, cinnamon and nuts together.
Remove one dough piece at a time from the refrigerator.
On a floured board, roll it into a 10-inch circle.
Spread with a thin layer of raspberry jam (about 1 tablespoon), leaving edges uncovered.
Sprinkle about 1/4 cup of the sugar/nuts mixture on the dough.
Cut the circle into 12 pieces to make 12 triangles.
Place 2 raisins at the uncovered edge of each.
Roll up each triangle, holding the tip and stretching as you go.
Be sure the edges are sealed.
Dip into the sugar/nuts mixture and shape into a crescent.
Place on a lightly greased cookie sheet in a preheated 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Repeat with remaining 5 dough pieces.

title: quick fruit cobbler
directions: Heat fruit or berries, juice, 1 cup sugar and butter on stove to boil.
Remove and put in baking dish.

title: tasty shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixer bowl.
Mix until well blended.
