Chill until serving time.

title: tuna balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except cornflakes and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in the crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Can also be frozen.
To thaw, heat in a 350° oven.
Serve with toothpicks and tartar sauce or tuna ball sauce.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs; blend together the sugar and flour, then stir into eggs and remaining ingredients.
Add milk last.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Watch until set and brown.

title: slush
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil; simmer 15 minutes, then cool. Add juices and gin, then freeze.
When ready to serve, fill glasses half full with slush.
Fill remaining half with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shells.
Chill and serve.

title: tomato lentil soup
directions: Place lentils, water, onion, carrots and celery in large pot. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer gently 2 hours.
(Add water if level gets too low.)
Add spices and stir.
Simmer another hour.
Stir in tomato paste.
Mix well.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Serve.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Make a syrup using the water and sugar; bring to a rapid boil, then reduce heat and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Set aside to cool thoroughly.
When cooled, add other ingredients.
Mix well and freeze.
When ready to serve, add frozen mixture, after thawing to a slush, to equal amount of ginger ale, about 4 large bottles. Serves 50.

title: bonnies' alphabet salad
directions: Cook macaroni and let cool.
Drain pineapple and oranges (save juice).
Beat eggs, add juice from pineapple and oranges, flour, sugar and salt.
Cook until thick then let cool (pudding consistency).
Mix macaroni, pudding mixture and cool whip.

title: potato bacon soup
directions: Spray pan with butter flavor pan spray and cook onions and bacon until tender.
Stir in water and cubed potatoes and cook until tender.
Slightly mash potatoes (leave some chunks).
Stir in milk, butter seasoning mix, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat about 10 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Swing by Schunuck's Deli, whip out your wallet.
Run through the express checkout.
Serve "as is".

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl with electric mixer.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: ice cream soda
directions: Pour soda into a very large glass.
Do not fill to the top. Carefully place ice cream into glass.
Mix with a spoon and enjoy.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in boiler.
Cook over medium heat until a small amount will form medium hard ball in cold water or until it will spin a thread when poured from a spoon 18-inches high.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook ground meat, onion and garlic until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain on paper towel.
Return to skillet and add remaining ingredients except spaghetti.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer over low heat for 45 minutes. Uncover and continue simmering 15 minutes until sauce is thick. Serve over spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.
One-thousand calorie recipe.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook beef and onions in heavy skillet.
Add all the other ingredients.
Mix well. Place in casserole dish and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peasant bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
In a large bowl, combine flours, salt and sugar.
Add the yeast mixture and remaining water; stir until combined.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Stir dough down.
Divide in half. Place each half in a greased 1-quart casserole or ovenproof bowl. Brush tops with butter or margarine.
Let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from pans; serve warm, if desired.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Then mix in order and cook over medium heat in Dutch oven, stirring often.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased casserole and bake until center is solid (test with knife).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain.
Mix all together except 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Place in large baking dish.
Sprinkle with the 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over the top, before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon fruit salad
directions: Mix the juices of the pineapple and mandarin oranges in the pudding. Pour over fruit and chill.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Put into graham cracker crust.
Top with whole can of pie filling. Chill.

title: breakfast strata
directions: Saute sausage and bacon; drain on paper towels.
Crumble. Place 1/2 of bread cubes, 1/2 of cheese and all meat mixture in dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cover with remaining bread and cheese.

title: best ever chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa.
Add egg yolks and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar; brown.

title: old fashion egg salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes two cups.

title: overnight broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package, omitting salt.
In frying pan or microwave, melt 1 stick margarine.
Add soup mix, pecans and water chestnuts.
Add to drained broccoli and mix well. Pour in casserole.
Cover overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beef, potato, onion casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Alternate layers of beef, potatoes and onions. Salt and pepper each layer.
In a bowl mix the milk, mushroom soup and wine.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and cook at 350° for 3 hours.

title: pepper relish
directions: Combine green tomatoes, ripe tomatoes, green peppers, red peppers, sugar and vinegar in large saucepan; mix well.
Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace; seal with 2-piece lids.
Process in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
May add chopped onion if desired.
Yield:
48 servings.

title: vegetable salad marinade
directions: Marinate all of the ingredients together for at least 2 hours. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: german cabbage soup
directions: Place cabbage, onion and stock in 2 1/2 quart saucepan. Pour lemon
juice
over apples to prevent discoloration.
Add chopped tomatoes,
apples,	salt and sugar to stock.
Cook 25 minutes. Add pepper.
Good to freeze.

title: sweet bread
directions: Scald milk with oleo and cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Add the cool milk to the sugar.
Beat eggs and add to milk and sugar.
Add salt and vanilla.
Mix well. Add half of the flour and mix well. Add yeast and rest of the flour.
Mix until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Put into greased bowl. Cover and raise until double.
Punch down.
Put into greased loaf pans. Raise until double. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: virgin brittle
directions: Line a jelly roll pan with foil. Lay crackers on foil to cover. Boil butter, margarine, sugar and vanilla for 2 minutes. Pour butter mix over crackers. Make sure crackers are all covered with butter mixture. Sprinkle corn flakes on top.
You can also add nuts or coconut.
Bake at 325 degrees for 20 minutes.
Pull foil out of pan onto protected counter to cool. This will peel off the foil when cool.

title: lunchbox sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and spread on bread. Refrigerate remaining mixture for next day.

title: pecan crisp
directions: Thoroughly cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop from teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients (except flour tortillas) together and spread over tortillas.
Roll up jellyroll style, refrigerate until firm enough to slice.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes for 10 minutes.
Cool and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add flour to onion. Remove from heat and add cream and Parmesan cheese.
Place potatoes in a shallow dish and pour mixture over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: milk chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In large bowl, mix flour, brown sugar and margarine until crumbly. Reserve 3/4 cup. Press remainder in ungreased 9-inch square or 11 x 7-inch pan. In same bowl, combine 2/3 cup reserved flour mixture, caramel topping, cream cheese, vanilla and egg. Blend at low speed until well mixed. Stir in nuts. Pour over crumb mixture in pan. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm. Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips. Spread when softened. Chill before cutting. Place leftovers in fridge.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Stir and cook sugar, corn syrup, water, butter and salt until sugar dissolves.
Continue cooking in pan, without stirring (270°), until syrup forms a brittle ball in cold water.
Now, add vanilla flavoring to mixture.
Pour over warm popcorn.
Shape into balls.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, butter and egg until fluffy and well blended. Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture with grated zucchini, blending well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until done.
Do not overbake.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: cherry kugel
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add sour cream, vanilla, salt and cherries.
Add noodles (do not overcook noodles).
Mix well.
Pour in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until light brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup and salad dressing together.
Add chicken, celery, almonds and onion.
Put into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole; top with herb dressing.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325° to 350°.
Scald milk.
Add bread cubes, sugar and salt.
Allow to cool 5 minutes.
Slowly pour mixture into bowl of beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and raisins or coconut, if desired.
Place mixture in well-buttered 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in shallow pan of hot water for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: southwest stew
directions: In skillet brown beef and onions.
Drain any excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered for 15-20 minutes.
Garnish with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: peppered flank steak
directions: Mix 1st
four ingredients and rub on steak, both sides. Let stand 5 minutes.
Broil or grill.
Slice thinly.

title: latkes (potato pancakes)
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients except oil.
In a large skillet, heat 1/4 inch of oil over high heat.
Drop
potato mixture by level tablespoonfuls into hot skillet.
Brown about 1 to 2 minutes per side.
Keep warm.
Repeat with remaining potato mixture.
(Can be made ahead.
Cool and refrigerate, covered, up to 24 hours.
Reheat on cookie sheets in a preheated 400° oven for 5 minutes.)
Makes 36 servings.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat egg, flour and sugar.
Add vinegar, cold water and nutmeg. Bake as a two crust pie in a medium oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cook in oven at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix these ingredients and pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 325 degrees for 35-40 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Cook onion and celery in margarine or butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring thoroughly.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: fresh corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, corn, sugar, salt and pepper.
Pour into casserole.
Stir in butter.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes stirring once after first 15 minutes of baking.

title: fast brownies
directions: Measure all dry ingredients together.
With electric mixer, combine remaining ingredients except nuts.
Add dry ingredients. (Add nuts last.)
Will be thick.
Bake in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
These are very good.

title: creamy hot turkey spread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot.
Crumble turkey into skillet, stir in green onions, garlic and seasoned salt.
Cook until turkey is no longer pink, stirring to finely break up turkey; drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream in medium bowl, stir in turkey mixture, olives and Tabasco sauce.
Spoon mixture evenly into pie plate, 9 x 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle with almonds; bake until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Spread on bread slices.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, onions and carrots in salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Save 1/2 cup of liquid.
Combine soup, sour cream, oleo and liquid.
Make stuffing; place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine vegetables and soup mixture; then place on top of stuffing.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shred chicken into pieces.
Crush crackers and mix in melted butter.
Spread 3/4 of crackers on bottom and sides of casserole dish.
Spread on chicken.
Heat both cans of condensed soup together.
Take off heat and fold in sour cream.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle remaining crackers on top. Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until lightly brown on top.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Crumble crackers.
Add baking powder and mix well.
Add milk; set aside.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Combine with cracker mixture.
Stir in vanilla extract, pecans and coconut.
Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Add mashed bananas, flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, milk, vanilla and chopped nuts. Pour mixture into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: mystery salad
directions: Puree tomatoes in a blender.
Dissolve jello in hot water. Mix tomatoes with hot sauce.
Blend with jello.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: country fried steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and salt.
Brown in skillet with hot oil. Add water and onion.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: egg salad sandwich
directions: Peel and mash eggs, using a fork or potato masher.
Add remaining ingredients and mix gently.
Chill before serving. Spread on your favorite bread for a great sandwich.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: randy's cheese cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch spring-form pan.
Cream eggs and cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in lemon juice, vanilla and sour cream, then add sugar and whipping cream; beat.
Cook 20 minutes at 400°.
Turn oven down to 275° and cook for 40 minutes.
Turn oven off and let cake cool in oven for at least 1 hour.

title: chocolate silk pie
directions: Beat margarine in a large bowl until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar until fluffy.
Mix in chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, beating for four minutes after each egg. Spoon into shell.
Chill for four hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Cover tightly and bake 5 hours at 250° or 300° or until meat and veggies are tender.
Serve on mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: easter tarts
directions: Roll out dough.
Cut circles to fit in cupcake tins.
Bake until done.
Fill with any pudding.
Add toasted coconut and a few jelly beans.

title: stuffed round steak
directions: Drain the liquid from mushrooms.
Combine with onion and bread crumbs.
Brown in oleo; add 1/4 teaspoon sage, salt and pepper. Flatten steak to 1/4 to 1/3-inch thick.
Spread mixture over meat and roll up, jelly roll style.
Fasten with skewers or string around roll and ends.
Roll steak in flour, season with salt and brown in hot oil in skillet or Dutch oven.
Add 1/4 cup water; cover and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add water as needed.
Make gravy to serve over steak.
If the steak is large, you can make two rolls, which is easier to handle for browning.

title: snappy glazed meatballs
directions: In medium bowl combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
In skillet, brown meatballs, turning occasionally; drain.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Pour sauce over meatballs; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve warm in chafing dish or electric frypan.
Makes about 4 dozen meatballs.

title: audrey's cherry supreme
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly dust with flour an 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine ingredients in the order listed.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Spoon Red Sauce over each serving.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large container.
Add ice to chill.
Serves 75.

title: pate a peas
directions: Heat butter and oil.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is soft.
Add all ingredients.
Warm in oven before serving (about 30 to 45 minutes).
Especially good served with roast beef.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Scramble eggs with a little milk and butter.
Lightly brown hash browns.
Cook ham or bacon.
Use lightly greased pan, 13 x 9-inches.
Add potatoes, meat, vegetables, eggs and cheese in layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can refrigerate overnight before baking.

title: doll salad
directions: Let the jello cool and add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Let set until firm.
Cook until thick pineapple juice, sugar, flour and 2 beaten eggs.
Let set until cool, then add Cool Whip.
Spread over jello.
Add shredded cheese over the top.

title: fluffy pot pie
directions: Mix
well.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into squares. Add to boiling ham broth.	Simmer 25 minutes, covered.

title: beef pot roast
directions: Coat pot roast with flour.
In Dutch oven, brown slowly on all sides in 2 tablespoons oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover tightly and simmer slowly 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Add water, if needed.

title: belle baganz's coffee cake
directions: Mix (cut in) first 3 ingredients until crumbly and remove 1 cup of mixture to sprinkle on top of batter.
To remaining mixture, add baking powder, eggs, milk and flavoring.
Add cinnamon to the cup removed and put on top of batter.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan (I use 9 x 13-inch pan) and bake at a moderate temperature for about 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Beat eggs and ingredients (except crab meat).
Add to crab meat and stir ingredients with fork, using an up and over motion. Pat into cakes.
Fry crab cakes until light brown in color.

title: krissy's holiday salad
directions: Lightly toss the first 5 ingredients.
Divide onto 4 plates, covered with lettuce leaves.
Place a large dollop of yogurt on top of each for dressing.

title: jailhouse chili
directions: Place
beans in a large saucepan.
Add 8 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Simmer until beans are almost tender (about 2 hours).
Drain and set aside.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add ground beef and cook until browned, breaking up pieces with a spoon.
Spoon off fat.
Add remaining ingredients
and
beans.
Heat
to boiling.
Reduce heat to simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: steak and potato supper
directions: Dredge steak with flour.
Heat oil in frying pan.
Brown steak on both sides in hot oil.
Add remaining.
Cover; simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Serves 4.

title: mrs. vice's apple salad
directions: Mix flour and sugar well.
Stir in whipping cream (not whipped).
Add pineapple juice and all.
Cook in thick boiler until thick (sticks easy).
Remove from heat and add butter and let cool some. Peel and dice apples.
Add apples and nuts to cooked mixture and mix.
Place 1/2 cherries on top.

title: cheese ball
directions: Wash dried beef to get rid of some of the salty taste.
Chop onion and dried beef.
By hand, mix all ingredients.
(Can spray hands with Pam for easier handling.)
Refrigerate cheese ball several hours in covered dish.

title: crab dip
directions: In large bowl mix cream cheese, sour cream, salad dressing, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and garlic salt until smooth.
Add enough milk to make mixture creamy.
Stir in 2 tablespoons of the grated cheese.
Fold crab meat into cream cheese mixture.
Pour into greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until mixture is bubbly and browned on top (about 39 minutes).
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 4 cups of dip.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender.
Cook potatoes and onions together until tender using chicken broth.
Blend cauliflower, potatoes and onions in blender.
Mixture should be thick.
Season with 1 tablespoon white pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Just before serving, add almost 1 pint of half and half to desired consistency.
Do not let boil.
Sprinkle parsley flakes over soup. Serves 6.

title: five cup salad
directions: Pour all of these into a bowl and stir it up.
Refrigerate a while and serve.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Put cookie dough in pizza pan, thin.
Don't overbake (any cookie recipe will work, such as the recipe on the chocolate chips bag or roll of sugar cookie dough at your grocery).
Bake and cover with Philadelphia cream cheese icing.
Combine cream cheese, butter, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Spread over cookie and add fruit, such as crushed pineapple (drained), bananas, kiwi, strawberries, mandarin oranges and maraschino cherries.
(Use your favorite fruit.
It is pretty if it is colorful.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Chop pretzels and mix with the margarine. Bake 10 minutes at 300° in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix the cream cheese and sugar. Fold in the Cool Whip.
Pour over pretzels and place in refrigerator until set. Dissolve the jello and water.
Add strawberries and pour over already set mixture.
Let set again.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan with canola oil spray.
Mix applesauce and egg whites in a large bowl.
Stir in yellow cake mix, Jell-O and lemon rind.
Slowly drizzle in pineapple juice.
Using a mixer, beat for 5 minutes. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake approximately 35 minutes or until done.

title: linda's cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together all ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Bake 1 hour.
May top with bacon bits before baking, if desired.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in rice and mix together.
Add soups and mix together.
Set chicken parts on top. Do not cover.
Do not add water.
Bake in oven at 275° for 2 hours.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Combine eggs, mayonnaise, flour and milk in the order listed. Then add ham, cheese, onion and broccoli.
Mix well and pour into 2 prepared pie shells.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 375°.

title: razzle dazzle raspberry
directions: Boil 3 cups water and dissolve Jell-O.
Add remaining 3 cups of water. Stir lemonade until melted. Combine lemonade and cranberry juice. Freeze this mixture in a freezer bag.
A few hours before serving, remove from freezer (should be slushy). Just before serving, add 7-Up and sherbet.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Pour ingredients into Tupperware 1-quart casserole.
Microwave at Medium for 3 to 5 minutes, until melted, stirring twice during this time.
Stir in 1 cup chopped nuts, if desired, and pour into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: candy popped corn
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to boil; boil 5 minutes.
Add soda and vanilla.
Spread popcorn and nuts in large roaster pan. Spread caramel mix over top; stir.
Bake 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Turn over mix every 15 minutes or 4 times.

title: cabbage-cauliflower salad
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a large bowl and stir up.
Place the remaining ingredients in the order given and store overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Toss just before serving. Serves at least 12.

title: cheezy taters and dogs
directions: Mix into ungreased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Pour cherry pie filling into an 8-inch glass pan or pie pan. Sprinkle with 1 cup cake mix.
Pour 1/2 stick butter or margarine (melted) over all.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Eagle brand milk and 1/2 c. milk then add vanilla pudding and let chill 5 minutes.
Add sour cream and cool whip.
Layer wafers, bananas, pudding and chocolate syrup.

title: moist fudge squares
directions: Grease 9-inch square pan.
Melt butter and chocolate.
When cooled a little, add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Then add flour and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: jack's italian chutney
directions: In pan; boil water, vinegar, and brown sugar until dissolved and smooth.
Add everything else and simmer with lazy bubbles for 2 hours or to this jelly like consistency

title: fig cupcakes
directions: Pour boiling water over figs.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Drain and dry.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in chopped figs.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15.

title: amaretto-chocolate mousse* * * * *
directions: The first time I made a chocolate mousse it was from a recipe of Julia Child's that I had seen her do on television.
It called for a raspberry sauce made with raspberry liquor.
Our little town does not have a liquor store, so I drove 10 miles to the closest one.
They didn't have it.
I had to drive 25 miles to the next one before I found it.
It cost $15.00.
Then I didn't have a suitable mold.
It cost $12.00.
Fresh raspberries were needed, at $6.00 a pint.
Finally I had everything I needed and proceeded to put the mousse together.
I dirtied every saucepan and most of my bowls.
If my time was worth anything, that mousse cost about $50.00.
It was delicious!

title: fruit ambrosia
directions: Fold mayonnaise into yogurt.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Cover.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute asparagus and onions in 1 tablespoon butter until crisp tender (about 8 minutes).
Transfer to ungreased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour until smooth; gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened. Reduce heat.
Add cream cheese, salt and pepper.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over vegetables.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Melt remaining butter; toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the sugar, oil and eggs in a bowl and mix well.
Sift the flour with soda and salt and stir into the sugar mixture.
Add the apples and 1 cup nuts and beat well.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Cool.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients well. Top with cheese. Just before heating, top with a generous layer of crushed potato chips. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
In a large casserole dish, crush one bag chips; sprinkle on the bottom of dish.
Add chicken on top of chips.
Melt cheese and soups on low heat.
Pour over chicken. Crush other bag of chips and put over top.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry goodin puddin
directions: Grease an
8-inch
pie
plate.
Spread cranberries over bottom.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and nuts.
Beat egg well. Add 1/2 cup
sugar and mix well.
Pour over cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 45
minutes
or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold with vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole 2
directions: Saute squash and onions in bacon drippings until tender. Drain.
Stir in sour cream, pimentos, soup and water chestnuts. Melt 6 tablespoons of butter in saucepan.
Add stuffing mix and mix well, reserving a small amount for topping.
Press stuffing mixture into a 2-quart baking dish.
Spoon squash mixture over stuffing.
Sprinkle reserved stuffing and bacon over squash.
Dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato rolls
directions: Mix sweet potatoes, sugar, pineapple and flavoring.
Take large marshmallows and put the sweet potato mix all around them. Roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Put balls in a greased dish and bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread unrolled crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Mix soft cream cheese, Ranch dressing, mayo and salad dressing.
Spread on baked rolls.
Dice onion very small and sprinkle on top of cream cheese mixture.
Add cut up vegetables and Cheddar cheese.
Keep refrigerated.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, boiling water, cold liquid and peaches.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with small marshmallows.
Let set until firm in refrigerator.
Blend cream cheese and pineapple.
Make Dream Whip according to instructions on the box.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Spread over top firm jello.
Top with cherries. You can also use strawberries and strawberry jello.

title: low-fat cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and stir well.
Best results if beaters used.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quiche
directions: Chop ham or bacon. Put in bottom of pie shell. Mix other ingredients and pour over ham.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Done when golden on top.
Yields 2 pies.

title: riz biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, soda and sugar. Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk. Cut shortening into flour mixture as for biscuits. Stir buttermilk into dry ingredients quickly.
Turn dough out onto floured cloth and knead just until smooth. Roll to 1/4-inch thick and cut with cutter. Brush top with butter.
Place one on top of the other, making double biscuits. Cover and let set in warm place about 1 hour.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt the oleo in a baking dish.
Add the peaches or fruit. Combine the remaining ingredients; mix batter until smooth.
Pour over peaches or fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Mix morsels in 2 quart casserole. Microwave 4 minutes, covered on high. Stir half-way through cooking. Remove from oven, stir in peanuts and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.

title: two minute pie
directions: Put first 3 ingredients together.
Put into pie shell and put shredded coconut on top.
Put in refrigerator for 1 hour or more.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Blend all ingredients except cream.
Whip the cream and fold into remaining ingredients.
Freeze 4 to 5 hours.
Raspberries are delicious.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together and pour into baking dish.
Set aside.

title: feather fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Melt and add chocolate.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add to cream mixture alternately with ice water. Pour into cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Combine milk and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Grease pan well. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: ripp's french applesauce
directions: Slice orange in half; squeeze one half and put other half to the side.
Mix applesauce with the orange juice.
Mix in about 1 teaspoon of cinnamon to the applesauce.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat with salt and pepper to taste.
Drain off fat. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Place 1 cup shredded Mozzarella cheese in meat and mix.

title: hamburg-sausage spread
directions: Brown Sausage and Hamburg.
Drain Fat.
Mix and add seasonings and velveeta.
Stir till cheese melts.
Spread on rye bread.
Put mozzarella on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 350.
Can be frozen.

title: meat balls
directions: Form
into
small
balls; cook in hot water in skillet. Drain water
and	brown.	Add to sauce and cook over low heat for 15 minutes to 1 hour.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Brown meat; drain excess fat.
Stir in tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Press dough in 12-inch pizza pan.
Stab the dough with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Top with ground meat and cheese.
Bake again for 10 minutes.

title: quick jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello.
Fold in Cool Whip and pineapple.
Serve chilled.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown sausage; add spaghetti sauce.
Pour the sausage and sauce into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Top with 1/2 pound Mozzarella cheese.
Mix together the flour, salt, milk and eggs; beat well.
Top cheese with flour mixture.
Add on top of flour mixture another 1/2 pound of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy steak
directions: Trim off fat and cut steak into serving size pieces; salt and pepper.
Put steak in baking dish or skillet with lid.
Add catsup, Coca-Cola or other cola drink, onion and bell pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Sauce may be thickened with flour, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil the broccoli until tender.
Take the butter saute the onion in it.
Add the cheese, rice and cooked broccoli.
Stir all together and place bread crumbs on top, patted with butter. Bake in microwave 5 to 7 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, soup and 1/2 cup onions in a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Return to oven and bake for 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: the classroom's roasted carrot and potato soup
directions: Peel and roughly cut the potatoes, carrots, garlic, celery and onion and place in roasting pan. Coat with butter, salt and pepper to taste, then mix thoroughly.

Roast in a 400° oven until vegetables brown slightly, about 30 to 45 minutes, depending on oven. Reduce temperature to 325° and roast until tender, about 1/2 hour more. Stir frequently to prevent scorching.

title: frozen caramel pie
directions: 1. Brown pie shells according to directions, then cool. 2. Brown pecans and coconut with butter in skillet. 3. Mix cool whip, cream cheese and condensed milk with mixer. 4. Combine ingredients for each pie- first spoon in 1/4 of the cream cheese mixture into the bottom of the pie shell. Then pour enough caramel topping to cover, then add a layer of the coconut and pecans. Repeat. Each pie will have two layers of all the ingredients. Serve frozen. Makes 2 pies.

title: macaroni and cheese(the grandchildren's favorite)
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Mix cheese, macaroni, eggs and milk. Be sure to have enough cheese to cover the top well.
Bake in a 300° oven about 30 minutes until cheese milk is well set.
Then broil at 400° until lightly browned, if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and mix well after each.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients; add water and mix all together.
Pour into two well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool.

title: date nut cake
directions: Melt
butter, pour over dates and nuts, pour flour over nuts and
add
eggs.
Mix
well.
Add
vanilla and pineapple. Bake at 300°
for 1 hour.
Spray pan with Pam or grease well. If
you want
fruit
added,
use
cherries	and mixed candied chopped fruit, like you use in a fruitcake.

title: uncle will's candy(bonbons)
directions: Mix together and chill.
Then make small balls. Dip in chocolate almond bark or chocolate chips.

title: deviled crab
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs, spoon int into 4 small buttered baking dishes (or regular casserole dish).
Sprinkle crumbs over crab mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 2 to 3 servings.

title: lemon parsley chicken and brown rice
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil.
Add chicken broth; bring to a boil. Stir in rice.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in parsley, lemon peel and pepper.
Cover; let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Serves 4.

title: tiger tea
directions: Boil 1 qt. of water, remove from heat, add tea bags.
Steep for 5 minutes.
Discard tea bags.
Stir in lemonade and orange juice concentrates, sugar and remaining water.
Serve over ice.
Makes approximately 3 quarts.

title: broccoli dip #2
directions: Cook broccoli according to instructions on package.
Melt cheese and mushroom soup together.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter.
Mix with cheese; add broccoli and seasonings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain and add taco seasoning.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add cheese.

title: string bean supreme
directions: Combine and let stand 1 hour.
Cover with buttered crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday ambrosia
directions: First
drain both fruits.
Reserve juice for other uses. Blend oranges and pineapple to sour cream.
Add coconut.
Stir in marshmallow bits.
Chill after blending.
Let sit at least 2 to 3 hours for flavor to form.
Delicious at Easter!

title: cherry pineapple delight
directions: Line a baking dish with whole graham crackers.
Mix 1/2 can of pineapple in with the small tub of Cool Whip and nuts.
Layer half on top of the graham crackers.
Layer another layer of graham crackers and rest of Cool Whip pineapple-nut mixture; top with cherry pie filling and crumble graham crackers on top.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: cheesecake
directions: Crush
zwieback
and
mix
well
with
soft butter and 2 tablespoons
sugar.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan and up the sides.
Mix
the 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Soften the cream
cheese
with a spoon.
Add the dry ingredients and cream together.
Separate the eggs.
Add vanilla and the unbeaten egg yolks;
beat.
Stir in the cream and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour
this mixture on top of the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cake cool.
Preparing time is 30 minutes.

title: marble cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: candy corn
directions: Cook margarine, sugar, Karo and salt until blended well and bubbly, at least 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and soda.
Stir in corn and spread on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 250 degrees, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook slowly until a soft ball forms in cold water, then let cool.
Add 1/4 stick of butter.
Add nuts and beat until it starts to thicken, then pour into buttered pan.

title: poinsettia cookies
directions: Melt butter, marshmallows and vanilla on low.
Add food coloring.
Mix in corn flakes.
Shape into wreaths on wax paper. Add red cinnamon candies around wreath; let set overnight.

title: chocolate "crazy" cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, mix well the first 5 ingredients. Make 3 holes in mixture.
In the first hole, put the vinegar, in the second hole put the cold water and in the third hole, put the oil.
Mix well; batter will be thin.
Bake at 340° for about 30 minutes.
Cut cake in pan.

title: becky's baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Add all ingredients except beans. Mix well.
Pour all ingredients, including beans, in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter-corn flake candy
directions: Combine
sugar and syrup in 3 1/2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil
on
medium
heat.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter. Add
corn
flakes
and
stir until all are coated with syrup mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Cook first 6 ingredients until done.
Melt margarine; add flour and milk, cooking until thick and bubbly.
Stir into the rest of the ingredients.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water. Put in 9 x 13 inch glass pan. Add strawberries. Set aside in refrigerator. Dissolve lemon jello in 1 cup boiling water. Add 1/2 cup pineapple juice. Stir in cream cheese and add pineapple tidbits. Fold whipped cream (already whipped and sweetened) into this. Put evenly on top of strawberry mixture and chill.

title: memphis corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: easy cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; let set for 24 hours.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a spoon.
Pour almost all the dough into greased loaf pan.
Put the whole cherries on top and cover thinly with remaining batter.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs in small pieces and roll in flour; brown quickly in butter, heated to sizzling point.
Place ribs in heavy aluminum pan.
To make barbecue sauce, mix onions, catsup, green pepper and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over spareribs; cover and bake over low heat for 1 hour.

title: cheese apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in a greased baking dish.
Add water and lemon juice.
Mix water and lemon juice.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, flour and salt.
Work in butter to form a crumbly mixture.
Add grated cheese to crumbly mixture.
Spread the mixture over the apples and bake in a moderate oven (350°) until apples are tender and crust is crisp.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Stir cheese soup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish until smooth. Gradually add milk.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy pasta and vegetables
directions: Cut unpeeled acorn squash in rings, peeled or scrubbed parsnips and carrots in quarters or lengthwise, scrubbed red-skinned or sweet potatoes in 1 1/2 to 2-inch chunks, and peeled onions in wedges.
Spread vegetables in single layer in 1 or 2 baking pans or baking sheets with sides.
Drizzle with vegetable oil, then sprinkle with salt, pepper and dried thyme to taste.
Bake in a 450° oven, turning every 10 minutes or so, for 30 minutes or until lightly browned and tender.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place potato slices in greased oblong baking dish; top with orange slices, then pork chops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper; sprinkle brown sugar.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours, uncovering last half hour.
Serves 6.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Place sliced apples in a buttered pie plate and drizzle with orange juice.

title: fruit pops
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour into 5 ounce paper cups and place a stick in each cup.
Freeze.

title: eggs and ham delight
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients.
Put in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(I always double this.) It's great for company brunch!

title: french toast for a brunch or crowd
directions: Slice French bread 1-inch thick.
Fit into a well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs well and add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle nutmeg or cinnamon on top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove foil and bake uncovered 45 to 50 minutes (350°) until puffy and light brown.
Dab with butter.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger; add tomatoes and green chillies. Put in crock-pot on low heat and add cheese.
Stir until melted.

title: crisp apple bake
directions: Cut together flour and butter and add oats, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Should be a crumbly texture; do not use beaters.
Place apples in buttered 8 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with oat mixture and pat gently into apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: garlic potato dish
directions: Skin, boil and mash the potatoes.
Mix in the garlic (pressed or crushed).
Add salt.
Let sit for at least 10 minutes.
Wire whisk in vegetable oil, vinegar and egg yolks.
Let sit for several hours in the refrigerator.
Lasts for a week or so.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook for 6 minutes in microwave.
Mix with mixer.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla and 1 cup chopped pecans. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: sausage and broccoli casserole
directions: Brown sausage; add to thawed broccoli, chopped onion and Cheez Whiz.
Add drained mushrooms, mushroom soup, melted oleo, instant rice and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch dish at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together. Make the night before.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix and pat in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup cornflake crumbs on top.
Pour 1/2 stick melted margarine over all.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: moselle's rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Scald milk and add sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add about 2 cups flour and beat thoroughly.
Add eggs and yeast; beat thoroughly.
Add rest of flour to make a soft dough.
Knead on a floured board until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Let rise until doubled.
Cut out in desired shapes and let rise until doubled again.
Bake at 425° until browned.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In large bowl, mix (stir) together flour, sugar and salt, if needed, real well.

title: diet cookies
directions: Cream oleo.
Beat egg with orange juice, rind, sweetener and vanilla.
Add to oleo.
Reserve 1 tablespoon flour.
Sift the remaining flour with salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Add sour cream.
Mix reserved flour with the nuts and raisins.
Stir into batter.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: stacie's rag doll salad
directions: Place peach 1/2 for body on salad plate.
Arrange celery sticks for arms and legs around peach.
Use large marshmallow for head, raisins for eyes, nose, shoes and buttons.
The small piece of maraschino cherry for mouth.
Put shredded cheese around the marshmallow for hair.
Add a skirt of leaf lettuce to complete the salad.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except bread crumbs and cheese. Place in greased 2-quart casserole. Top with bread crumbs, then cheese. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° until bubbly and brown on top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot crunchy turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Mix cheese and chips and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except brown sugar, together.
Pour into greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle top heavily with white sugar and brown sugar.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. (Best when served warm.)

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl, then make a well in the center.
Add all of the liquid at once and stir well.
Set aside for 45 minutes to an hour until dough begins to rise well.
Add enough flour until easy to handle.
You may roll the dough, then cut it into pieces or simply tear off a piece and slap or mold it with your hands to the desired shape and thickness, about 1/4-inch.
Fry in hot oil.
The oil will be hot enough when a small piece of dough is dropped into it and it begins to bubble and comes to the surface.
After brown on one side, turn and brown on the other.
Drain on paper towels.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt
butter
in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat sugar and water until sugar
melts.
Cut
shortening
into
flour.
Add milk. Knead
a little.
Roll until 1/4-inch thick.
Top with apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll like jelly roll.
Slice into 1/2-inch
slices and
place
in pan with melted butter.
Pour sugar syrup carefully around rolls.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pineapple fudge
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, pineapple and cream in well-buttered heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until candy reaches soft ball stage (236°).
Remove from heat; add butter.
Do not stir.
Cool until saucepan feels lukewarm.
Add vanilla.
Heat until candy begins to thicken.
Beat in nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
As candy firms, it will lose slick look and become creamy.
Cool and cut.
Makes about 3 dozen pieces.

title: black pepper and onion scones
directions: Saute onion in 1/4 cup butter.
Mix flour, sugar, pepper, baking powder and salt. Add egg, whipping cream and onion just until moistened.
On floured board, knead dough gently 5 to 6 times.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press into 8-inch circle, 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into light wedges.
Pull apart a little.
Lightly brush with butter.
Bake 12 to 16 minutes at 400°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat first five ingredients until light and fluffy.
Then fold in the pineapple tidbits.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly in a very large bowl, by hand!
Be careful; don't make a cocoa dust cloud, like I did first time I made this mix.
Store in airtight container; makes a lot and keeps well.
I use a gallon jar with a wide lid.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with chicken spread. Add soy sauce and chives or parsley.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in Saran Wrap. Chill overnight.
Roll in nuts if desired.

title: cod
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a shallow baking dish large enough to hold fish in a single layer.
Season fish with salt and pepper.
Place in prepared dish.
Arrange lemon slices on fillets; sprinkle with scallions, then top with sage leaves.
Dot with butter.
Pour broth into dish.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, basting occasionally, with pan juices just until fish is opaque at its thickest part.
Serve fish with pan juices spooned over.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, soft cream cheese, pineapple and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Put into a large bowl, a layer of vanilla wafers, then pineapple pudding and a thin layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat again. The last layer, all Cool Whip.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add to the potato chip mixture and mix well.
Stir in the pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet, allowing space for the cookies to spread. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned. Makes 5 dozen.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Let set overnight.
Mix in mayonnaise before serving.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine egg and milk; stir in flour and salt.
Stir in corn and make a fairly thin batter.
Drop by tablespoons and fry 3 or 4 at a time in heavy saucepan until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels and keep fritters warm in 200° oven while frying remaining cakes.
Makes 10 fritters.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour in bowl and top with the following:
Tortilla Chips, Shredded cheese, Salsa, Onions (optional), Shredded lettuce, Diced tomatoes, Sour cream (Can be frozen up to 3 months).

title: old south spoon bread
directions: Combine salt and corn meal; add slowly to boiling water, stirring constantly to prevent lumping.
Combine vinegar and milk. Add 1 1/2 cups of vinegar and milk to corn meal mixture.
Mix well. Add eggs and melted shortening.
Stir until well blended.
Dissolve soda in remaining vinegar and milk.
Add to corn meal mixture and stir until completely blended.

title: cream puff pastry
directions: Combine water and butter in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add flour and salt, all at once, stirring vigorously over medium-high heat until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth ball.
Remove from heat and cool 4 to 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly with a wooden spoon after each addition, then beat until dough is smooth.
Drop Cream Puff Pastry into 8 equal mounds 3 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and puffed.
Cut off tops and pull out soft dough.
Fill with pudding. Put tops back on.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and shape in a loaf pan.
Put catsup on top. Do not let run down sides and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: celebration spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil.
Saute zucchini, mushrooms and olives.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, Parmesan cheese, salt, basil and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti.
Drain.
Toss with softened butter.
Arrange on warm platter.
Pour on sauce and top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese 2 to 3 minutes with mixer until smooth.
Add vanilla, beat in part of sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat until light and creamy.
Pour into crust and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Save 2 teaspoons graham crackers for top.
Remove from oven and let stand for 15 minutes.
Turn oven to 450°.
Mix sour cream, vanilla and remaining sugar together.
Spread evenly on top. Sprinkle with crumbs, then chill and serve.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain.
Add soup and then 2 cans of water.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: banana split brownie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix.
Pour brownie mixture in buttered square Pyrex dish.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.
Enjoy on any favorite cracker.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Mix potatoes, soup, onions, sour cream and cheese together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Drizzle melted butter on top of cornflakes.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: calico cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage, discard heart.
Combine all ingredients and toss slightly.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: frying pan balls
directions: Mix first two ingredients in frying pan over low heat until mixture leaves sides of the pan.
Then add Rice Krispies, vanilla and salt.
Mix and let cool for 10 minutes.
Take mixture and roll 1-inch balls, then roll into chopped nuts.

title: fireman's fish
directions: Defrost and squeeze spinach of all water.
Spread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Layer sole fillets on top of spinach. In large saucepan, thoroughly heat just to boiling, tomatoes, garlic, dill and lemon juice.
Cook 15 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Pour sauce over fish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish is done.

title: mexican pizza dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Spread the 2 cans beans on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next, spread the avocado mixture over beans.
Mix the sour cream, mayo and taco seasoning. Spread over the avocado mixture.
Add green pepper, onion, tomato and olives.
Spread cheese over entire dip.
Serve with Doritos.

title: raspberry custard
directions: Combine.
Bake at 475° for 5 minutes, then at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: campfire cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie filling.
Pour into a 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour pie filling on top.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: caribbean lemon chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in large plastic food storage bag. Combine teriyaki sauce, lemon peel, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce and cinnamon.
Pour over chicken.
Press air out of bag; close top securely.
Turn bag over several times to coat chicken well. Refrigerate overnight, turning bag over occasionally.
Remove chicken and broil or grill 5 to 7 inches from heat source for 40 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Turn occasionally during cooking.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in shortening.
Add water.
This is a very good pie crust; never fails.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight containers.
To use, fill cup 1/2 full of mix.
Fill with boiling water.
Good with miniature marshmallows added.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix all well, then put into pie shells.
Chill overnight and that's it.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Heat milk; remove from heat.
Add all ingredients.
Mix well. Form into soft ball.
Let rise 1 hour.
Grease casserole dish. Punch bread down.
Put into dish.
Cut X in top.
Let rise 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.
Makes 1 round or 2 loaves.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; take off bone and place in a large baking dish.
Pour 2 cans cream of chicken soup over meat.
Mix one package Pepperidge Farm dressing mix, 2 eggs, onion and 3/4 cup evaporated milk.
Pour over soup.
Pour chicken broth over dressing to about 1/2 inch over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party mix
directions: Mix melted butter, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and salt.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to butter mixture.
Coat all and bake 2 hours at 250°, stirring every 30 minutes.
Shut oven off and leave in until cool.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Set aside.
Sift salt, soda and flour together.
Add mashed bananas alternately with the flour mixture to the shortening mixture.
Bake in 1 regular or 2 small loaf pans for 1 hour at 300 degrees or until toothpick comes out of the center clean.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse.
Stir in chicken, Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
If dry, you may want more soup or cheese.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until cheese is bubbly.

title: missouri cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute; then add the oatmeal and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonful.
Let set about 2 hours.

title: cranapple mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O completely in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until melted.
Add applesauce.
Pour into greased mold.
Refrigerate until set, unmold onto plate.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop pecans, dates and candy slices.
Add coconut.
Pour melted oleo over mixture and let stand while preparing batter. Beat eggs; add sugar and then other ingredients.
Mix well with fruit and candy.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 2 hours at 300°.

title: diabetic rice salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.

title: saucy beans
directions: Saute bacon and onion until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook for 15 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown the ground chuck; drain off the fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: mile high hot cakes
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff and put in refrigerator.
In second bowl, beat egg yolks and yogurt well. Sift flour, salt and baking soda; add to egg yolk and yogurt mixture.
Stir in milk and honey.
Carefully fold in egg whites. Cook on hot griddle, flipping when batter bubbles.
Yields 12 medium pancakes, thick and cake-like.

title: alta's rolls!!!
directions: Mix together 2	cups
water, sugar and salt.
Add yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup water.
Stir in eggs and shortening.
Mix in the flour first
with
spoon
and
then
by hand.
When the dough begins to leave
the sides of the bowl, turn it out onto a lightly floured
board
and
knead.
Knead	until
dough
is smooth, elastic and
doesn't
stick
to
board.
(If you use a mixer with a dough hook, this step is eliminated.) Place dough in a greased bowl,
turning once to bring oiled side up. Cover with a damp cloth
and	let
rise
until
double
1/2 to 2 hours).	 Punch down,
pull
edges
into
center
and
turn completely over in bowl.
Let rise until almost double (30 to 45 minutes).
Shape into
rolls.
Let rise until light (15 to 20 minutes).
Bake at 425° for 12 to 20 minutes, depending on size of rolls.
(Cinnamon rolls may be made with dough.)

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot water.
Add cranberries, pineapple, juice and nuts.
Stir well and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Peel cooked potatoes, add margarine (I use Parkay), sugar, milk, eggs, and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer until fluffy. Put in large well-greased baking dish.
Bake about 40 minutes in 300 degree preheated oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Hand mix all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Test with a toothpick.

title: guillott's eggplants
directions: Peel and cut up eggplants.
Add 1 cup water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover and cook 15 minutes.
Add sugar, margarine and cinnamon.
Stir well.
Cook slowly 20 minutes more, stirring occasionally, until completely cooked.

title: sandies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Cream the butter until fluffy; gradually add sugar, beating until smooth.
Beat in water and vanilla. Alternately add flour and nuts, blending after each addition. With lightly floured hands, roll dough in small balls or date-shaped pieces.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, about 1-inch apart.
Bake for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar as soon as taken from oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add unbeaten egg and beat vigorously.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with the applesauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown.
Store in tight container.
They will stay moist.
Put in refrigerator and they will keep indefinitely.

title: beer bread(dry mix)
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in beer until moist.
Turn into well-greased loaf pan, then bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Pour melted butter over loaf and bake another 10 minutes.
Enjoy warm.

title: chicken broccoli rice
directions: In a skillet, in hot margarine, cook chicken, half at a time, until brown. Add broccoli and carrots. Cook until tender-crisp. Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fluff with fork before serving.
Makes 4 servings.
Preparation time:
10 minutes. Cooking time:
30 minutes.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream together in mixer:
butter, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and egg.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Drop into well-greased and floured 1 1/2-inch muffin pans.
Bake at 325° for about 12 minutes until golden (looks like little muffins).
Remove from oven and immediately press 1 miniature peanut butter cup in the center. Cool in refrigerator 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove cookies from muffin pans with sharp knife.

title: mushroom onion pot roast
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place large sheet of heavy-duty foil on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Spoon mushroom soup over it and seal all edges with foil.
Bake 3 hours.

title: oven roast
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour over roast in covered pan. Bake at 250° for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.
Serve with rice since makes great gravy.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour can of milk over bread crumbs.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cut up 2 tablespoons of margarine and put on top of pudding.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jiffy chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt; add to other ingredients.
Beat hard for 3 minutes.
Bake in greased 8-inch pan for 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Blend tomatoes, soup, onion, chilies, salsa and seasoning. Mix in blender or food processor until well mixed into a sauce. Crumble tortilla chips.
Layer chips, 1/2 chicken, 1/2 sauce and 1/2 cheese in a casserole dish; repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or microwave on High 15 minutes.
Top with sour cream or guacamole.

title: apple crisp #1
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put apples in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cinnamon, water and lemon juice.
Mix remaining ingredients with fork until crumbled.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: biscuit barbecups
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 muffin cups.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each muffin cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Beat in sugar.
Add oil slowly and beat well. Add vanilla.
Sift flour and measure; sift again with dry ingredients.
Add minced zucchini.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 50 minutes at 350° or until done.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: captain richard's dandy fish chowder
directions: Prepare fish.
Combine with all other ingredients, except cream, milk and butter; simmer until fish is cooked.
Place cooked ingredients in a large pot.

title: baked sandwiches
directions: Combine ham, cheese, onion, eggs and olives; blend with mayonnaise and chili sauce.
Spread on 6 or 8 buns.
Wrap buns individually in aluminum foil.
Place on baking pan or cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry parfait
directions: Sprinkle strawberries with 1 cup of sugar.
Let stand several hours.
Strain through a fine sieve.
Pour into a refrigerator tray.
Freeze until slightly icy.
Put in a saucepan 1 cup of sugar and water; boil until syrup spins a thread (about 5 minutes).
Beating constantly, pour the syrup slowly over the egg whites and keep beating until the mixture is cool.
Fold in the heavy cream.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients together and add alternately with syrup.
Add vanilla. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with any chocolate frosting you like.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water with 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Mix all other ingredients with the buttermilk and warm water.
Pour in the dissolved yeast.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Make out rolls.
Let rise 1 hour before baking. Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: any color angel salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except gelatin together.
Pour as much gelatin in for however much color you want.
The cherry, lime or orange gelatin makes a pretty color.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: To make filling, heat chicken, onion and 5 ounces green enchilada
sauce
until
onion is tender.
When the filling is ready, put 3 cups of water, the chili powder and vegetable oil in a
saucepan
and
bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer. Using tongs,
tip tortillas in the simmering water just until the tortilla is soft.
(If the tortillas stay in the water too long they
will
tear
when
you
make the enchiladas.) Place tortilla in
a
greased
pan
and
fill with a small amount of filling
and grated
Monterey Jack cheese.
Wrap the tortilla around
the filling (like a crepe).
Repeat this process with each
tortilla, dividing the filling and Monterey Jack cheese among
the
12 tortillas.
Place the enchiladas in a row, and pour
remaining green sauce over them.
Lay sliced Velveeta on the enchiladas. Cover with foil and heat at 375° until cheese melts
(about 20 minutes).
For spicy enchiladas, add 1 tablespoon chopped jalapenos to chicken filling.

title: spanish bean soup
directions: Soak garbanzos overnight with a tablespoon of salt and enough water to cover beans.
When ready to cook, drain the salted water from the beans and put in the ham bone and beef bone with 2 quarts of water.
Cook for 45 minutes on slow fire.
Fry bacon and onions (onions having been chopped fine).
Place these in the pot, adding potatoes, saffron and salt.
When potatoes are done, remove from fire and add chorizo cut in thin slices.

title: turkey sweet potato soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine sweet potatoes, celery, onion, marjoram, thyme, cayenne pepper, water and chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in turkey, peas and bacon. In small bowl, combine cornstarch and milk; blend well.
Slowly stir into soup; cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Makes six 1 1/3 cups servings.

title: chocolate-cinnamon angel cake
directions: Bring egg whites to room temperature (about 1 hour). Meanwhile, sift flour, powdered sugar, cocoa powder and cinnamon together 3 times.
Set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk until hot.
Add to bread crumbs and butter or oleo in bowl.
Combine sugar, salt and raisins with slightly beaten eggs.
Then slowly add to hot mixture.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4.

title: aunt june's molasses cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Chill. Form 1-inch balls and roll in sugar. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: ground beef pinwheels
directions: Shape biscuit dough into ball.
Roll into 8 x 14-inch rectangle.
Combine next 5 ingredients in bowl, mixing well. Spread evenly on dough.
Roll as for jelly roll from long side. Slice in 1-inch thick pieces.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Add peas and carrots to prepared gravy, mixing well.
Pour over pinwheels. Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put onions into food processor or blender and blend until mushy on medium speed.
Add lemon juice and honey.
Combine dry spices, except poppy seed, and add to onions.
Slowly pour oil into blender until mixture is thick and smooth.
Add poppy seed and process only a few seconds longer.
Makes 2 cups.

title: corn flake kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Add sugar gradually (not all at once) to beaten egg whites.
Add salt and orange extract.
Fold in cornflakes and coconut.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet.
Drop from a teaspoon and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool in pan until firm or bottoms will gum.
Makes approximately 2 1/2 dozen.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt butter in 2 quart saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients except chocolate chips.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and pepper salad
directions: In medium bowl, gently stir together chicken and peppers. In cup, stir together oil, vinegar, basil, oregano and garlic. Pour dressing over chicken and peppers.
Toss gently and serve on salad greens.

title: fresh strawberry ice cream
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, salt and flour in medium saucepan; add milk gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Stir half the mixture slowly into beaten eggs in bowl; stir back into remaining mixture in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Remove from heat; pour into a large bowl and cool.
Stir in cream; chill.

title: breaded onions
directions: Blend oil and flour.
Add milk and egg.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Batter will be thin.
Dry food thoroughly, then coat generously with unseasoned flour.
Dip into batter, letting excess drip off.
Fry in oil at 375° in skillet or heavy skillet.
Oil one-inch deep, but pan not more than 1/3 full.
Fry golden brown.
Drain.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add flour; stir until smooth.
Add milk; stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients; let it heat until hot.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, to 268° on candy thermometer or to hard-ball stage.

title: orange-spiced pork chops
directions: In a small bowl combine sugar, cumin, chilli, dry mustard, orange zest, salt and pepper.
Rub both sides of pork chops with spice mixture.
In a large skilled heat oil over medium high heat. Add pork chops, cook turning once until golden brown which is about 6 to 7 minutes per side.
Decorate with orange slices and freshly cut up parsley.

title: banana shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Then cover and mix at high speed until foamy.
Makes 1 serving.

title: israeli chicken
directions: Slice onion, celery and carrots and pour juice and wine and spices.
Marinate chicken for an hour.
Fry chicken parts in oil lightly.
Arrange in baking dish and pour marinade mixture on top. Cover with foil and bake for an hour at 350°.
Add raisins and bake another 30 minutes, uncovered.
Put chicken on serving plate. Add reduced sauce and decorate with orange slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: vegetable pasta
directions: Saute the garlic and onion in the olive oil.
Add the zucchini, yellow squash and mushrooms.
Add the basil and oregano. Before serving, add the noodles to the vegetables.
Stir-fry for a minute with vegetables.
Serve immediately with Parmesan cheese.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine crackers, onion rings and salt in bowl.
Chill, covered, for 45 minutes to 1 hour; drain.
Add pepper, vinegar and sour cream, stirring to coat.
Chill for several hours or longer to enhance flavor.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Stir 1 cup pecans with all ingredients.
Chill for about 30 minutes.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Keep refrigerated until serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: peanut buttered popcorn
directions: In large roasting pan, combine popcorn and almonds; keep warm in 250° oven.
Butter sides of heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Combine sugar, honey and corn syrup in pan.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil hard for 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla until blended. Immediately pour over popcorn mixture, stirring to coat well; cool.
Break into bite-size pieces.
Makes 3 quarts or 36 snack servings.

title: bazetti
directions: Brown meat.
Add vegetables and 1 tablespoon water.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add cooked noodles, mushrooms and soup.
Top with cheese.
Cover pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: fattigmands bakkels
directions: Heat deep fat to 375°.
Beat egg yolks, whole egg and salt until very stiff, about 10 minutes.
Blend in confectioners sugar and flavorings thoroughly.
Add flour all at once and mix well. Knead dough on well floured cloth-covered board until surface is blistered in appearance, about 7 minutes.
Divide in half; roll out each half very thin.
With pastry wheel, cut dough into 4 x 2 diamonds.
Make 1-inch slits in center of each; draw a long point of diamond through slit and curl back in opposite direction.
Fry until delicately browned in deep hot fat, about 30 seconds.
Turn quickly and brown on other side; drain.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar just before serving.

title: swedish baked rice
directions: Cook rice in salted water until done.
Blanch and drain. Place rice and 3 cups milk in double boiler. Separate the eggs; beat the yolks well.
Add sugar, cornstarch and one cup milk.
Add to the rice and cook until thick. Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add the almond flavoring.
Place in buttered baking dish.

title: strawberry and banana delight
directions: Bake cake according to the directions. Mix pudding according to the directions on box. Slice strawberries and mix with sugar. Slice the bananas. Put 1 cake layer in big bowl. Layer the pudding, bananas, Cool Whip and strawberries. Do the same with the next layer until you end up with Cool Whip and strawberries on the top. Chill in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: lemon broiled lamb leg
directions: Rub lamb with garlic, ginger, salt and pepper.
Pour juice of 1 lemon on lamb.
Brown lamb under broiler, turning often to brown evenly, far enough away from flame so it doesn't brown too fast, about 30 minutes.
Remove from broiler and place in roasting pan; brush with remaining lemon juice and roast for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.

title: five bean bake
directions: Brown the meat and drain.
Drain all the beans, except for the pork and beans.
Saute celery and onions.
In a large bowl, add and mix all ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with tomato paste and sliced bacon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pot roast dinner
directions: In skillet, brown roast well.
Transfer to roaster pan, then add vegetables.
Mix water and soup mix.
Pour over this.
Salt and pepper well.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.

title: cocoa coconut oatmeal nests
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar until blended well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Combine together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture beating until blended.	Stir in oats and coconut.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly, remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.

title: brown sugar coffee cake
directions: Mix all until crumbly.
Take out 1 cup of crumbly mixture for top of cake.

title: pierogi(little pies)
directions: Boil potatoes; drain and mash.
Add American cheese.
Cut onion fine.
Brown in butter and add to potatoes.

title: todd's salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with instant pudding.
Add all remaining ingredients and chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: With mixer beat cream cheese until it is creamy.
Add the other ingredients and mix together.
Serve with fruit.

title: turkey casserole
directions: In an 8-inch square baking dish, layer broccoli and top with turkey.
In a small bowl, combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over turkey and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: light waffles
directions: Combine
flour,
sugar
and
soda in a large bowl.
Add buttermilk
and oil to dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff
peaks
form,
fold
into batter.
Coat your waffle iron with
vegetable cooking spray every time you need to pour more batter in waffle iron.
Makes 32 waffles.
