title: easy strawberry smoothie
directions: Place first four ingredients in blender.
Mix until smooth. Add crushed ice to create desired consistency and blend.
Add wheat germ and protein powder for a healthy breakfast drink. Serves 2 to 4.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Blend all ingredients except cream cheese and mayonnaise together.
Mix cream cheese with just enough mayonnaise to give good spreading consistency.
Add vegetables.
Use thin sliced bread.
Great for parties.

title: bacon-egg casserole
directions: Brown bacon and dry off fat.
Add eggs (do not beat) and crumbled bread; add milk, salt and cheese and toss lightly.
Pour into greased baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes and cut in squares.

title: toffee bars
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 jellyroll pan. Mix all ingredients except egg whites and walnuts.
Pat evenly in a jellyroll pan.
Beat egg white and brush on dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut 4 strips lengthwise and 12 strips across to make 48.
Remove from pan.
Store in covered container.

title: banana bread(great for gift giving)
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add bananas, sour cream, soda and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture.
Also add pecans, if desired.

title: beef stew
directions: Bring to a boil and cook on low heat for 2 hours.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Break 1 head lettuce in bite size pieces.
Slice celery and spread over lettuce.
Slice and separate onion.
Spread over celery.
Peel and slice cucumber.
Spread over onion.
Sprinkle with bean sprouts.
Combine sour cream with sugar.
Drizzle over salad.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and cool 20 minutes.
Add next 6 ingredients, mix and set aside.
Sift dry ingredients and add to liquid mix.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan and cut in squares.
Stays moist.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cacciatore sauce
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute onions and mushrooms with garlic powder in margarine until onions are transparent. Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Makes 2 cups.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix all
ingredients
together;
add Mountain Dew last. Bake in 3 layers at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Combine in saucepan over low heat the butter and milk.
When butter melts, beat in powdered sugar, cocoa and vanilla.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour with spices and soda. Add buttermilk.
Stir in jam last.
Bake in two 9-inch pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: c. y. o. b. mix(choose your own booze)
directions: In small saucepan, combine water, sugar, cinnamon and cloves; bring to boiling.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes. Strain out spices and discard.
Chill syrup.
In glass pitcher, combine apple juice, nectar, lemon juice and the chilled spiced syrup.
Add lemon slices.
To serve, pour 1 jigger of your favorite liquor over ice in a glass.
Add C.Y.O.B. mix; stir. (Makes about 4 1/2 cups mix.)

title: irish soda bread
directions: Combine milk and vinegar.
Set aside until the rest is mixed. Mix all dry ingredients:
flour, salt, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, caraway seeds and raisins.
Mix lightly with a fork.
Add the milk with the vinegar.
Put in pan to bake.
Melt butter, some sugar.
Spread on top of dough.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sausage nuggets
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix together.
Make balls (size of walnuts).
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes.
These may be made ahead and stored in freezer.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix.
Add bananas and mix.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf (one large) pan.
Cook at 375° for 15 minutes.
Lower to 350° and cook for 45 minutes longer.

title: oatmeal drop cookies(so good they don't keep.)
directions: Combine flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt; cream shortening with sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs and vanilla and blend; add dry ingredients.
Fold in coconut, nuts and oats. Drop from teaspoon onto slightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Cool and store in airtight container.

title: pecan meringues
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Add vanilla, sugar, salt, and spices. Beat until very stiff. Add pecans and fold in gently until all halves are coated evenly. Place each half on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 250 for about 20 minutes or until dry and can be slipped of pan. Let cool in pan and remove. Store in air tight container.

title: refrigerator muffins
directions: Soak and set aside shredded wheat, All-Bran and boiling water. Cream sugar and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add to soaked ingredients.
Store in a covered jar or dish in refrigerator or bake at once.
Can store at least 4 weeks.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, the water, oat bran, vinegar, brown sugar, chili, Worcestershire sauce, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Scald (do not boil) 1 quart of whole milk; reserve a cup of that milk.
Mix to that cup of milk the flour, cornstarch, egg yolks and salt until smooth.
Pour in remaining quart of scalded milk.
Cook this batter 10 to 12 minutes, stirring constantly. Add sugar and cook 10 to 12 minutes more, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add 1 quart of whole milk and strain through strainer.
Cool batter until cold (this can be done by sitting bowl in ice in sink).
Add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then fold in custard.
Last, add whipping cream and table cream. Crank as usual in freezer with ice and rock salt.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain grease.
Put in large baking dish.
Mix soup and 1 can chicken broth.
Make it a little soupy.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle cheese on top of meat and soup. Place Tater Tots all over.
Bake until Tater Tots are brown at 400°.

title: aunt ange's chicken
directions: In plastic bag, add flour, salt and pepper. In a bowl, beat eggs and salt and pepper with a little bit of milk. Shake chicken in flour and take out and dip in egg. Fry in electric skillet in vegetable oil at 350°. Enjoy.

title: grandma's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Add 1 or 2 catsup bottles of water and simmer.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: When fryer is tender, take out of broth.
Take meat off bone. Add flour to 1 cup of hot water until thick enough to put on wax paper.
Add more flour until stiff enough to roll out thin.
Cut in strips; drop in broth.
Don't stir, just move around when done. Set aside until cool, then put lid on pot.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread; spread each lightly with margarine.
Cut each slice into 4 lengthwise pieces.
Arrange toast crosswise, buttered side down, forming a single layer.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and apple.
Continue layering 2 more times.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place by tablespoonful on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine and flour in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cheese and onions.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove foil and bake an additional 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook cornbread according to package directions.
Boil squash and drain off water.
Crumble cornbread and mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and chill.
Drain beans and chill.
Dice onion, slice tomatoes into wedges, grate lettuce, mash avocado and add beef and beans.

title: gourmet skillet steak
directions: In large shallow baking dish, pour Italian dressing over beef. Cover and marinate in fridge, turning occasionally, 4 hours or overnight.

title: sausage skillet express
directions: Combine sausage, celery and onions in a large skillet; cook over medium heat, stirring often, until vegetables are tender. Drain well.
Add the next 6 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit ripple cookie cake
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients except for pie filling. Spread half of batter in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan that has been greased on the inside bottom.
Top with pie filling of your choice.
Dollop remaining batter over fruit, covering as much filling as possible.
Swirls in batter and fruit peeking through are to be expected.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until browned.
Serve warm.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Wash rice.
Combine meat, rice, salt, pepper and onions.
Shape into small balls.
Heat sauce and water in pressure cooker.
Drop meatballs in sauce mixture.
Cook for 10 minutes at 15 pounds or simmer for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: stewed spareribs with pineapple
directions: Soak pineapple in light salty water.
Drain.
Cut into pieces. Wash, wipe dry and chop spareribs into 1-inch lengths. Add marinade and let it set for 20 minutes. Deep fry spareribs in hot oil until they turn light brown.
Drain excessive oil.
Set aside.

title: garden vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Cool and drain. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Let cool overnight.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Sift together, flour, soda and salt. Mix shortening and sugar together.
Add egg, vanilla and water.
Slowly mix in dry ingredients.
Add oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by small tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and boil together for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add oatmeal, peanut butter and nuts. Mix together and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, brown beef.
Remove meat; set aside.
In same skillet, saute onion in butter until onion is translucent.
Drain fat.

title: mother rote's gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar, vegetable shortening and egg together.
Add the molasses, sifted flour, salt and cinnamon; blend well.
Add boiling water and soda.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp roll
directions: Thoroughly mash together and form into log.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: easy lemon cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into prepared crust.
Allow to set overnight in refrigerator.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa, milk and butter to a boil.
Have oats in a mixing bowl with peanut butter on top in middle.
Pour boiling mixture over peanut butter and oats.
Mix fast and well.
Spoon out on wax paper, will set up in an hour.

title: scooterpooters
directions: Heat oven to 350 -375 degrees.
Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, 1 + 1/2 cups sugar, eggs, and applesauce. Sift flour and gradually add to mixture.
Stir in chopped apples (semi-large chunks).

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Melt chocolate bits over hot water.
Beat egg whites and dash of salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat whites to stiff peaks.
Fold in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in chocolate bits and chopped nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove immediately.
Makes 36.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet or casserole.
Mix dry ingredients, add broccoli and eggs.
Mix well and pour in casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: fried okra or squash
directions: Cut squash or okra in slices.
Mix meal, flour and salt.
Pour on top of okra or squash and batter.
Heat oil in pan, then add battered squash or okra.
Fry on medium-low until brown.

title: angie's deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs lengthwise in half.
Remove yolks.
In medium bowl, crush yolks.
Mix with all ingredients, except paprika.
Fill eggs with yolk mixture.
Sprinkle eggs with paprika and chill.

title: ziti and cheese bake
directions: Prepare ziti as directed; place in large bowl.
In 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, into 3 tablespoons butter stir flour; cook 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk; cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens slightly.
Stir in Fontina, Port du Salut and pepper.
Pour cheese mixture over ziti; with rubber spatula, gently stir to coat ziti well.
Spoon 1/2 mixture into deep 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with Mozzarella.
Spoon on rest of ziti mixture. Melt 1 tablespoon butter and mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350° until top is golden.

title: easy chicken
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
When chicken is done, remove meat from bone.
Cut into bite size pieces.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix milk with soup and pour over chicken.
Mix broth with stuffing and spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Pour a little more broth over the casserole before covering and baking to make sure it won't dry.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Press crescent rolls into 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, basil leaves and garlic powder.
Spread thinly over cooled crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Sprinkle generously with Salad Supreme

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: little fish birthday cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, with electric mixer on high, beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes.
Add egg, corn syrup, and vanilla, and beat 1 minute. Reduce mixer speed to low and beat in flour and salt until combined.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a disk.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in large baking dish with lid. Layer in order:
green beans, salt and pepper to taste, can of tomatoes, onion rings and bacon (to cover beans).
Makes at least 2 layers or 3 is better.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
When done, bacon on top will brown.
Makes 12 or more servings.

title: dream pie
directions: Melt first two ingredients together.
Melt candy bars into mixture.
Let cool.
Add 1/2 of Cool Whip. Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours. Pour in shell, then add rest of Cool Whip.
Keep cool.
Serve.

title: * boiled spice raisin cake *
directions: Boil sugar, water, raisins, oleo, cinnamon, soda and cloves for 3 to 6 minutes.
Cool, then add flour and baking powder.
Nuts may be added, if desired.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pat a pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Combine canola oil and skim milk. Add to flour mixture.
Stir gently.
Pat thinly into a 9-inch pie plate, building up top edge.
Flute edge.
Fill and bake according to recipe directions.
Or for a baked shell, prick crust and bake in a 450° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 1 crust.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix as for fruit cake.
Drop by small teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake slowly (300°).

title: apple crisp(microwave recipe)
directions: Place apples in dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice, if desired. Combine 1/4 cup sugar, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1 tablespoon flour in small bowl.
Toss with apples to coat.
Combine flour, oats and brown sugar and cinnamon in mixing.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cook on Full power for 11 to 13 minutes or until tender.

title: corn chowder
directions: Grind first 3 ingredients together.
Combine all together and cook 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix in oats, chocolate chips and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 5 dozen.
Kids love em!

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch. Add yolks of eggs to paste.
Add water gradually.
Boil.
Add butter and vanilla. Fill baked pie shell. Top with meringue and brown in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip candy
directions: Combine water and rolled oats; cool.
Cream butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla; beat in eggs.
Blend in oatmeal mixture. Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Beat one minute at medium speed.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle your chosen amount of chocolate chips on top; do not stir.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Let sit until cool; sprinkle on powdered sugar.
Last, but not least, hurry and eat it before someone else does!

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add chocolate and vanilla, blending well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 5 minutes, after each addition, on medium speed.
Pour into prepared baked 8-inch pie shell and refrigerate.
Cover with whipped cream at time of serving.

title: elegant raspberry sauce
directions: Place raspberries in blender container or food processor bowl; cover and blend until smooth.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Blend well.
Costs only a fraction of canned sweetened condensed milk, such as Eagle Brand.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all other ingredients together.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; place half of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters. Put 1/2 of sugar and all of cinnamon in plastic bag. Drop biscuits into bag and shake to coat. Drop biscuits into a tube pan. Melt butter and remaining sugar. Pour over
biscuits. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes.

title: noodles
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour.
Add flour until kneading consistency.
Put on flour board or counter top and continue to knead and add flour until ready to roll.
Roll to thinness desired and let stand 10 minutes.
Flour good and roll.
Slice thin and tenderly shake out.
Let stand 10 minutes then cook in broth for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness.
Mix bread crumbs and 4 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumb mixture.
In a large skillet, heat oil (about 3 to 4 tablespoons) and brown the chicken on both sides.
Remove from skillet and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place a slice of Mozzarella cheese on each piece, then pour spaghetti sauce over.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese and garlic salt.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 15 minutes.
Broil for a few minutes to brown.
Serves 4.

title: mexican dip
directions: Add beans, tomato sauce, taco seasoning, onion, green pepper and chili powder to cooked ground beef. Spread on a large round platter. Top with sour cream, avocado dip, shredded lettuce, grated Longhorn cheese, diced tomatoes and sliced black olives. Serve as a dip with tortilla chips.

title: eggplant-cheese casserole
directions: Cook eggplant, celery and onion with salt and pepper in a small amount of water.
Drain and mash.
Add cream sauce, raw eggs, mushrooms, almonds and grated cheese.
Pour in casserole dish and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until well set.
This serves 12 people.

title: steak and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut meat into 8 serving pieces, trimming fat and bone.
On wooden board or waxed paper using meat mallet or edge of saucer, pound mixture of flour, salt and pepper into meat.
In large, heavy skillet over medium heat in hot oil, brown meat well on both sides.
Arrange meat in 3-quart casserole.
Place carrot and potato slices on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and cover with 3 1/2 cups of water.
Bake, covered, 2 hours or until meat is fork-tender.
Skim off any excess.

title: chocolate chip marshmallow
directions: Put marshmallow between 2 cookies. May be heated in microwave for 10 seconds or until warm.
Enjoy.

title: butterscotch pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and margarine.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture alternating with milk and flavoring.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.

title: minestrone
directions: Boil water.
Heat oil in skillet and add onion, garlic, leeks, carrots and green beans.
Saute vegetables over low heat for about 6 minutes.
Add sauteed vegetables to boiling water.
Also, add potatoes, tomato sauce and stewed tomatoes.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 30 minutes.
Add zucchini, cabbage, beans and pasta.
Bring soup back to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Add parsley and basil. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish servings with Parmesan cheese.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash until tender; drain well.
Saute onion in oleo.
Mix with squash.
Add crumbled Ritz crackers, eggs, seasonings and cheese.
Put this into baking dish.
Mix oleo and cracker crumbs; put over top of squash.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef until done, stirring to break up into small pieces.
Drain well.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Allow to cool. Combine beef, drained beans, onions, chilies, olives and tomatoes. Put lettuce in large bowl and top with beef-bean mixture. Sprinkle on cheese and taco chips.
Pour dressing over all.
Toss well.
Serve at once.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and thickens. Stir a little of the hot mixture into the egg yolk and return to hot mixture.
Stirring constantly, bring just to boiling. Cool thoroughly. Beat well with electric mixer.
Add vanilla. Fold in whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all together and heat just to boiling.
Simmer and enjoy!

title: chicken with spinach
directions: Slice each chicken cutlet crosswise in half.
Chop enough spinach to equal 2 tablespoons.
Reserve remaining to line platter.
Slice mushrooms into quarters.

title: sausage and biscuit roll
directions: Roll biscuits out with edges overlapping.
Spread with sausage; cover with shredded cheese.
Roll up tight; wrap in aluminum foil and freeze for 15 minutes.
Take out and cut in small circles and bake in oven for about 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 small greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Or bake in convection oven at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, squeeze out the liquid.
Mix all of the ingredients together and chill for 24 hours.
Do not judge flavor until after 24 hours.

title: red velvet cake icing
directions: Mix milk, flour and salt.
Cook until thick.
Cool completely. Beat sugar and butter at high speed until fluffy.
Add cooled mixture.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Ice cool cake.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts between layers and top.

title: hot stuffed mushrooms
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush cleaned mushroom caps with melted butter.
Stuff and place in a well buttered baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring cornstarch, jello, sugar and water to a boil. Boil until mixture thickens. Take off heat and cool. Pour in strawberries and pour into crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter bars unbaked
directions: Melt margarine and add powdered sugar, peanut butter, graham crackers and vanilla.
Mix well.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips.
Add 1 or 2 tablespoons peanut butter.
Pour over bars.
Refrigerate.

title: baby pizza hors d'oeuvres
directions: Fry sausage.
Melt cheese into sausage.
Add onions and seasonings; stir thoroughly.
Spread on party rye.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze 24 hours.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: * I use broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Place jello in large dish and pour boiling water over it. Stir to dissolve.
Add pineapple and strawberries, using juice from both.
Slice bananas into mixture.
Add nuts and stir gently until mixed.
Place in refrigerator until it jells.
Spread Cool Whip over top before serving.

title: orange rolls
directions: *Fresh zest is worth the bother, but the peel from a bottle will work.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Spread graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Bring to boil sugar, margarine and salt to boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Add nuts or crispies to mixture.
Pour over graham crackers while hot then bake 10 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: cornbread muffins
directions: Mix all together; if too thick, add water to thin.
Bake at 400° until brown on top.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: hearty beef & vegetable soup
directions: Place water, 1 Tbsp. salt and bouillon in large pot and bring to a boil.
Add cabbage, onion, carrots, celery and tomatoes.
Cut beef into bite-size pieces and add to soup.
Return to boil, lower heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer covered for 3-4 hours.
Tastes even better the next day.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt butter in a large pot.
Add onions and cook until glassy. Drain tomatoes, reserving half the juice.
Cut up tomatoes and add with juice to onions.
Add chilies and flour and bring to a boil.
Add Velveeta cheese and melt slowly.
Serve in a fondue pot.
You can add 1 pound browned hamburger, if desired.

title: curry chicken
directions: Wash chicken in 2 cups of water and vinegar.
Pat dry. Marinate chicken in black pepper, seasoned salt, garlic powder, soy sauce, thyme and curry powder for about 2 hours.
Heat cooking oil in skillet.
Place chicken in skillet until slightly brown. Add marinade along with 2 cups water, onions and potatoes.
Simmer on low heat until chicken is fully cooked.
Serve over rice.

title: wiener in puff pastry
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Form into a ball.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, take a portion at a time, roll thinly and use the pastry to wrap around hot dogs. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until brown.
These may be made ahead of time.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 60 hot dogs.

title: english sherry trifle
directions: Slice half the sponge roll into 1-inch squares or rounds (or use ladyfingers) into bottom of glass bowl.
Soak with half the sherry.
Layer with fruit salad (reserve the cherries), 3 sliced bananas, the remainder of the sponge roll and finish with half a cup of sherry.

title: ham and macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions, using 1/2 cup extra milk.
Mix in casserole dish with ham, broccoli and soup.
(Optional:
Top with sliced American or shredded cheese.) Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Blend into creamed mixture to make a stiff cookie dough.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie dough on a pizza pan.
Let cool.
Spread Cool Whip over crust.
Slice fruit on top and arrange nicely.

title: taffy
directions: Cook until 250° or firm ball stage.
Add wax after cooking, then pull it until about white.
Eat!

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer sauerkraut and noodles in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Next, layer onion and corned beef.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and mustard; pour over layers.
Sprinkle with cheese and then bread crumbs.
Slice margarine over bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Sprinkle mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon over this, then add remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red or green pepper jelly
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and boil for 6 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in fruit pectin and continue to boil 3 more minutes.
Remove from heat.
Skim off foam.
Pour into hot sterile jars.
Makes about 7 half-pints.

title: hot fruit
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in an ovenproof dish.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Put raisins in hot water to soak first; drain.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or more.
Insert knife into center.
If clean, it is finished.
Before baking, place into a pan of water for baking.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine jello, water and 7-Up, then whip in Philadelphia cream cheese.
Fold in pineapple and nuts.
Put into mold and chill until firm.

title: wanda's ice cream bars
directions: Mix pudding and milk together until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Spread mixture on graham cracker squares.
Top each with another graham cracker square.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, put in freezer bags.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in an 8 x 8 x 2 ungreased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in pan and simmer one hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine everything except your cracker crumbs.
Pour into a casserole dish sprayed with a nonstick spray.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato relish
directions: Chop all vegetables in medium sized cubes.
Drain juice from tomatoes.
Put juice in container.
Add balance of ingredients to juice and mix well.
Add chopped vegetables and store in jars in refrigerator.
This relish is uncooked.

title: crisp dilled beans
directions: Stem green beans and pack uniformly in hot, sterilized jars. To each pint, add 1/4 teaspoon red pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill.
Heat together water, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; pour over beans.
Seal at once.
Makes 4 pints.

title: dream punch
directions: Whip sherbet and 7-Up until consistency of thick cream.
Serve in punch bowl.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Saute chicken, onion, and garlic in oil until chicken is done and onion soft on low heat.
Add tomatoes, Hunt's sauce, and all seasonings.
Stir.
Add green peppers in strips.
Bring to a boil and simmer 30 minutes covered.
Add rice, cover and let stand until rice is done.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooker. Cover. Cook on low 6 to 10 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.

title: apricot fried pies
directions: Cook apricots with 1 cup water and 1 cup sugar (for use next day).
Make pie crust mix as directed on box.
Roll until 1/4-inch thick.
Make small rounds.
Drop 1 large spoon of apricot mixture on each round.
Fold to middle.
Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 450° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar icing.

title: beef and cabbage soup
directions: Cook beef, onion and celery in a large Dutch oven over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain meat mixture in a colander.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Return meat mixture to pan.
Add cabbage, carrots, spices, chicken broth and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 1 hour or until carrots are tender.
Serves 16.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave.
Stir in condensed milk, nuts and vanilla. Stir well. Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square pan which has been lined with waxed paper.
Refrigerate for 2 hours, then cut into squares.
You can keep it out of the refrigerator but store in a cool place.

title: banana pudding
directions: In big bowl, add vanilla pudding and 3 cups of water and mix until soupy, then add condensed milk and 3/4 bowl of Cool Whip. May need to add more water for soupy pudding.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Chill about 1 hour.
Form into small balls; roll in sesame seed.
Place on oiled cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
(Optional: Gently push almonds into center of each cookie.)
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until it is done.
Let it cool.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Add as much vegetables as desired. Refrigerate.

title: chocolate tea bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Beat on low speed just until blended; stir in nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pretzel strawberry dessert
directions: Crush pretzels and mix with 1/2 c. sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 by 13 pan and bake 325° 5-6 min.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese until creamy and add cool whip and 1/2 c. sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add strawberries.
Let stand until it thickens, pour over cream cheese mixture.
Let stand several hours.
Serve with additional cool whip.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Precook 9-inch pie shell.
Cool.
Mix and cook first 3 ingredients until thick.
Add jello; stir until smooth.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell. Refrigerate.
